1
00:00:31,614 --> 00:00:34,325
[FEMALE WHISPERS IN ELVISH]

2
00:00:34,534 --> 00:00:37,620
FEMALE VOICE:
<i>The world is changed.</i>

3
00:00:37,787 --> 00:00:40,790
<i>I feel it in the water.</i>

4
00:00:41,541 --> 00:00:44,460
<i>I feel it in the earth.</i>

5
00:00:46,045 --> 00:00:49,048
<i>I smell it in the air.</i>

6
00:00:49,465 --> 00:00:51,342
<i>Much that once was...</i>

7
00:00:51,551 --> 00:00:53,135
<i>...is lost.</i>

8
00:00:53,803 --> 00:00:56,847
<i>For none now live who remember it.</i>

9
00:01:09,777 --> 00:01:14,156
<i>It began with the forging
of the Great Rings.</i>

10
00:01:14,407 --> 00:01:16,325
<i>Three were given to the Elves:</i>

11
00:01:16,492 --> 00:01:20,288
<i>Immortal, wisest and fairest
of all beings.</i>

12
00:01:21,330 --> 00:01:23,416
<i>Seven to the Dwarf-lords:</i>

13
00:01:24,166 --> 00:01:28,588
<i>Great miners and craftsmen
of the mountain halls.</i>

14
00:01:29,046 --> 00:01:30,298
<i>And nine...</i>

15
00:01:30,506 --> 00:01:33,509
<i>...nine rings were gifted
to the race of Men...</i>

16
00:01:33,718 --> 00:01:37,555
<i>...who, above all else, desire power.</i>

17
00:01:39,223 --> 00:01:43,894
<i>For within these rings was bound
the strength and will to govern each race.</i>

18
00:01:45,396 --> 00:01:48,566
<i>But they were all of them deceived.</i>

19
00:01:48,816 --> 00:01:50,901
<i>For another ring was made.</i>

20
00:01:52,278 --> 00:01:55,323
<i>In the land of Mordor,
in the fires of Mount Doom...</i>

21
00:01:55,740 --> 00:02:00,202
<i>...the Dark Lord Sauron forged
in secret a Master Ring...</i>

22
00:02:00,411 --> 00:02:02,455
<i>...to control all others.</i>

23
00:02:02,663 --> 00:02:06,626
<i>And into this Ring he poured
his cruelty, his malice...</i>

24
00:02:06,834 --> 00:02:11,047
<i>...and his will to dominate all life.</i>

25
00:02:12,006 --> 00:02:15,885
<i>One Ring to rule them all.</i>

26
00:02:16,719 --> 00:02:18,387
<i>One by one...</i>

27
00:02:18,596 --> 00:02:23,267
<i>...the Free Lands of Middle-earth
fell to the power of the Ring.</i>

28
00:02:23,476 --> 00:02:26,520
<i>But there were some who resisted.</i>

29
00:02:26,979 --> 00:02:31,651
<i>A Last Alliance of Men and Elves
marched against the armies of Mordor.</i>

30
00:02:31,859 --> 00:02:36,489
<i>And on the slopes of Mount Doom, they
fought for the freedom of Middle-earth.</i>

31
00:02:49,293 --> 00:02:50,920
[SPEAKS ELVISH]

32
00:03:06,811 --> 00:03:09,438
<i>Victory was near.</i>

33
00:03:14,193 --> 00:03:15,945
<i>But the power of the Ring...</i>

34
00:03:16,779 --> 00:03:18,197
<i>...could not be undone.</i>

35
00:03:42,805 --> 00:03:44,724
<i>It was in this moment...</i>

36
00:03:44,932 --> 00:03:47,309
<i>...when all hope had faded...</i>

37
00:03:47,518 --> 00:03:51,647
<i>...that lsildur, son of the king,
took up his father's sword.</i>

38
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:29,226
<i>Sauron, the enemy of the Free Peoples
of Middle-earth, was defeated.</i>

39
00:04:36,108 --> 00:04:38,277
<i>The Ring passed to lsildur...</i>

40
00:04:38,486 --> 00:04:42,698
<i>...who had this one chance
to destroy evil forever.</i>

41
00:04:43,407 --> 00:04:45,534
<i>But the hearts of Men...</i>

42
00:04:45,743 --> 00:04:48,245
<i>...are easily corrupted.</i>

43
00:04:48,496 --> 00:04:53,125
<i>And the Ring of Power
has a will of its own.</i>

44
00:05:18,317 --> 00:05:20,945
<i>It betrayed lsildur...</i>

45
00:05:22,780 --> 00:05:25,199
<i>...to his death.</i>

46
00:05:29,370 --> 00:05:33,249
<i>And some things
that should not have been forgotten...</i>

47
00:05:33,457 --> 00:05:35,793
<i>...were lost.</i>

48
00:05:36,627 --> 00:05:38,838
<i>History became legend...</i>

49
00:05:39,046 --> 00:05:41,048
<i>...legend became myth.</i>

50
00:05:41,257 --> 00:05:44,134
<i>And for
two and a half thousand years...</i>

51
00:05:44,301 --> 00:05:48,013
<i>...the Ring passed
out of all knowledge.</i>

52
00:05:48,639 --> 00:05:51,475
<i>Until, when chance</i> came...

53
00:05:52,142 --> 00:05:55,271
<i>...it ensnared a new bearer.</i>

54
00:05:56,605 --> 00:06:01,443
GOLLUM:
My precious.

55
00:06:01,694 --> 00:06:04,238
FEMALE VOICE: <i>The Ring came
to the creature GOLLUM...</i>

56
00:06:04,405 --> 00:06:08,325
<i>...who took it deep into the tunnels
of the Misty Mountains.</i>

57
00:06:08,617 --> 00:06:11,495
<i>And there it consumed him.</i>

58
00:06:11,745 --> 00:06:13,789
GOLLUM:
It came to me.

59
00:06:13,998 --> 00:06:18,419
My own. My love. My own.

60
00:06:18,627 --> 00:06:23,340
My precious.

61
00:06:26,969 --> 00:06:30,389
FEMALE VOICE: <i>The Ring brought
to GOLLUM unnatural long life.</i>

62
00:06:30,598 --> 00:06:34,435
<i>For 500 years it poisoned his mind.</i>

63
00:06:34,643 --> 00:06:39,231
<i>And in the gloom of Gollum's cave,
it waited.</i>

64
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:42,693
<i>Darkness crept back
into the forests of the world.</i>

65
00:06:42,943 --> 00:06:45,779
<i>Rumor grew of a shadow in the East...</i>

66
00:06:45,988 --> 00:06:48,782
<i>...whispers of a nameless fear.</i>

67
00:06:48,991 --> 00:06:52,286
<i>And the Ring of Power perceived...</i>

68
00:06:52,494 --> 00:06:55,289
<i>...its time had now</i> come.

69
00:06:57,708 --> 00:07:00,377
<i>It abandoned GOLLUM.</i>

70
00:07:01,045 --> 00:07:05,549
<i>But something happened then
the Ring did not intend.</i>

71
00:07:06,383 --> 00:07:10,971
<i>It was picked up by the most unlikely
creature imaginable.</i>

72
00:07:11,180 --> 00:07:12,222
BILBO:
What's this?

73
00:07:12,431 --> 00:07:13,891
FEMALE VOICE:
<i>A Hobbit.</i>

74
00:07:14,058 --> 00:07:16,810
<i>Bilbo Baggins of the Shire.</i>

75
00:07:17,019 --> 00:07:18,771
A ring.

76
00:07:18,979 --> 00:07:20,856
<i>GOLLUM:
Les“</i>

77
00:07:23,609 --> 00:07:27,071
My precious is lost!

78
00:07:27,279 --> 00:07:29,573
FEMALE VOICE:
<i>For the time Will soon</i> come...

79
00:07:29,823 --> 00:07:34,995
<i>...when Hobbits will shape
the fortunes of all.</i>

80
00:07:39,750 --> 00:07:42,836
BILBO:
The 22nd day of September...

81
00:07:43,003 --> 00:07:44,213
...in the year 1400...

82
00:07:46,423 --> 00:07:48,050
...by Shire-reckoning.

83
00:07:49,426 --> 00:07:54,139
Bag End, Bagshot Row, Hobbiton,
West far thing...

84
00:07:55,516 --> 00:07:56,892
...the Shire...

85
00:07:57,059 --> 00:07:59,895
...Middle-earth.

86
00:08:04,525 --> 00:08:07,861
The Third Age of this world.

87
00:08:19,415 --> 00:08:23,419
<i>There and Back Again:</i>

88
00:08:23,961 --> 00:08:25,796
<i>A Hobbit's Tale.</i>

89
00:08:25,963 --> 00:08:28,465
By Bilbo Baggins.

90
00:08:34,722 --> 00:08:36,473
Now...

91
00:08:37,182 --> 00:08:39,184
...where to begin?

92
00:08:40,477 --> 00:08:41,520
Ah, yes...

93
00:08:45,983 --> 00:08:47,693
"Concerning...

94
00:08:49,361 --> 00:08:50,529
...hobbits."

95
00:08:51,655 --> 00:08:55,200
<i>Hobbits have been living and farming
in the four Farthings of the Shire...</i>

96
00:08:55,367 --> 00:08:57,369
<i>...for many hundreds of years...</i>

97
00:08:57,536 --> 00:09:00,497
<i>...quite content to ignore
and be ignored...</i>

98
00:09:00,706 --> 00:09:03,876
<i>...by the world of the Big Folk.</i>

99
00:09:04,209 --> 00:09:09,882
<i>Middle-earth being, after all,
full of strange creatures beyond count...</i>

100
00:09:10,049 --> 00:09:13,218
<i>...Hobbits must seem
of little importance...</i>

101
00:09:13,385 --> 00:09:17,431
<i>...being neither renowned
as great warriors...</i>

102
00:09:17,598 --> 00:09:21,810
<i>...nor counted among the very wise.</i>

103
00:09:23,312 --> 00:09:25,773
[KNOCKING]

104
00:09:26,190 --> 00:09:29,193
Frodo! Someone at the door.

105
00:09:30,402 --> 00:09:32,946
<i>In fact, it has been remarked by some...</i>

106
00:09:33,197 --> 00:09:37,659
<i>...that Hobbits' only real passion
is for food.</i>

107
00:09:37,993 --> 00:09:40,204
<i>A rather unfair observation...</i>

108
00:09:40,370 --> 00:09:44,083
<i>...as we have also developed a keen
interest in the brewing of ales...</i>

109
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:47,211
<i>...and the smoking of pipe-weed.</i>

110
00:09:47,669 --> 00:09:50,506
<i>But where our hearts truly lie...</i>

111
00:09:50,672 --> 00:09:52,841
<i>...is in peace and quiet...</i>

112
00:09:53,509 --> 00:09:55,677
<i>...and good, tilled earth.</i>

113
00:09:55,844 --> 00:10:01,058
<i>For all Hobbits share a love
of things that grow.</i>

114
00:10:04,186 --> 00:10:08,607
<i>And, yes, no doubt to others,
our ways seem quaint.</i>

115
00:10:08,816 --> 00:10:14,029
<i>But today of all days,
it is brought home to me:</i>

116
00:10:14,613 --> 00:10:20,494
<i>It is no bad thing
to celebrate a simple life.</i>

117
00:10:22,246 --> 00:10:23,622
[KNOCKING]

118
00:10:24,706 --> 00:10:27,876
Frodo, the door!

119
00:10:31,713 --> 00:10:32,923
Sticklebacks. Where is that boy?

120
00:10:33,882 --> 00:10:35,551
Frodo!

121
00:10:41,390 --> 00:10:44,893
MALE VOICE:
<i>Down from the door Where it began</i>

122
00:10:46,562 --> 00:10:48,939
[WAGON RUMBLES]

123
00:10:49,606 --> 00:10:53,402
<i>And I must follow if I can</i>

124
00:10:54,403 --> 00:10:58,490
<i>The road goes ever on and on</i>

125
00:10:58,740 --> 00:11:02,244
<i>Down from the door where it began</i>

126
00:11:02,411 --> 00:11:07,374
<i>Now far ahead the road has gone</i>

127
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:11,795
<i>-And I must follow if! can</i>
-You're late.

128
00:11:15,090 --> 00:11:18,886
A wizard is never late, Frodo Baggins.

129
00:11:19,636 --> 00:11:24,308
Nor is he early. He arrives
precisely when he means to.

130
00:11:35,652 --> 00:11:38,780
It's wonderful to see you, Gandalf!

131
00:11:42,618 --> 00:11:46,330
You didn't think I'd miss
your Uncle Bilbo's birthday?

132
00:11:47,998 --> 00:11:50,167
How is the old rascal?

133
00:11:50,667 --> 00:11:54,213
I hear it's going to be a party
of special magnificence.

134
00:11:54,421 --> 00:11:56,840
You know Bilbo.
He's got the whole place in an uproar.

135
00:11:57,007 --> 00:11:59,009
Well, that should please him.

136
00:11:59,176 --> 00:12:01,011
Half the Shire's been invited.

137
00:12:01,303 --> 00:12:03,931
And the rest of them are turning up
anyway.

138
00:12:07,059 --> 00:12:10,395
<i>BILBO:
And so life in the Shire goes on...</i>

139
00:12:10,562 --> 00:12:13,649
<i>...very much as it has
this past Age...</i>

140
00:12:13,815 --> 00:12:19,363
<i>...full of its own comings and goings,
with change coming slowly.</i>

141
00:12:19,529 --> 00:12:21,448
<i>If it comes at all.</i>

142
00:12:22,699 --> 00:12:26,161
<i>For things are made to endure
in the Shire...</i>

143
00:12:26,328 --> 00:12:29,831
<i>...passing from one generation
to the next.</i>

144
00:12:30,207 --> 00:12:35,212
<i>There's always been a Baggins
living here under the Hill...</i>

145
00:12:35,379 --> 00:12:36,713
<i>...in Bag End.</i>

146
00:12:39,508 --> 00:12:42,344
And there always will be.

147
00:12:43,011 --> 00:12:46,390
To tell you the truth,
Bilbo's been a bit odd lately.

148
00:12:47,849 --> 00:12:50,018
I mean, more than usual.

149
00:12:51,019 --> 00:12:52,980
He's taken to locking himself
in his study.

150
00:12:54,523 --> 00:12:58,694
<i>He spends hours poring over old maps
when he thinks I'm not looking.</i>

151
00:13:11,373 --> 00:13:13,041
Where's it gone?

152
00:13:39,568 --> 00:13:41,903
He's up to something.

153
00:13:50,037 --> 00:13:52,539
- All right, then. Keep your secrets.
- What?

154
00:13:52,748 --> 00:13:54,416
But I know you have something
to do with it.

155
00:13:54,624 --> 00:13:55,751
Good gracious me.

156
00:13:55,959 --> 00:13:58,253
Before you came along, we Bagginses
were very well thought of.

157
00:13:59,087 --> 00:14:00,088
Indeed.

158
00:14:00,422 --> 00:14:02,591
Never had any adventures
or did anything unexpected.

159
00:14:03,175 --> 00:14:09,097
If you're referring to the incident
with the dragon, I was barely involved.

160
00:14:09,264 --> 00:14:12,851
All I did was give your uncle
a little nudge out of the door.

161
00:14:13,060 --> 00:14:17,105
Whatever you did, you've been officially
labeled a disturber of the peace.

162
00:14:17,564 --> 00:14:19,441
Oh, really?

163
00:14:25,072 --> 00:14:27,032
Gandalf! Gandalf!

164
00:14:27,741 --> 00:14:30,619
[CHILDREN SHOUTING]

165
00:14:33,121 --> 00:14:34,373
FEMALE HOBBIT 1:
Fireworks, Gandalf!

166
00:14:37,459 --> 00:14:40,045
FEMALE HOBBIT 2: Gandalf!
MALE HOBBIT: Fireworks, Gandalf!

167
00:14:58,897 --> 00:14:59,940
Gandalf?

168
00:15:00,482 --> 00:15:04,611
- I'm glad you're back.
- So am I, dear boy.

169
00:15:09,074 --> 00:15:10,826
So am I.

170
00:15:28,969 --> 00:15:31,471
Whoa, whoa.

171
00:15:42,691 --> 00:15:44,192
BILBO:
No, thank you!

172
00:15:44,359 --> 00:15:48,321
We don't want any more visitors,
well-wishers or distant relations!

173
00:15:48,530 --> 00:15:52,033
And what about very old friends?

174
00:15:55,203 --> 00:15:56,872
Gandalf?

175
00:15:57,539 --> 00:16:01,042
- Bilbo Baggins.
- My dear Gandalf!

176
00:16:01,209 --> 00:16:06,381
Good to see you. 111 years old!
Who would believe it?

177
00:16:08,133 --> 00:16:10,135
You haven't aged 3 day.

178
00:16:16,725 --> 00:16:18,727
Come on, come in!

179
00:16:18,894 --> 00:16:21,354
Welcome, welcome.

180
00:16:22,522 --> 00:16:25,066
Oh, here we are.

181
00:16:26,735 --> 00:16:29,196
Tea? Or maybe something
a little stronger?

182
00:16:29,362 --> 00:16:33,158
I've got a few bottles
of the Old Win yard left. 1296.

183
00:16:33,366 --> 00:16:37,412
Very good year. Almost as old as I am.

184
00:16:38,580 --> 00:16:43,084
It was laid down by my father.
What say we open one, eh?

185
00:16:43,251 --> 00:16:45,921
Just tea, thank you.

186
00:16:50,258 --> 00:16:52,093
Oh!

187
00:16:52,260 --> 00:16:53,929
I was expecting you sometime
last week.

188
00:16:54,179 --> 00:16:57,432
Not that it matters. You come and go as
you please. Always have and always will.

189
00:16:57,682 --> 00:17:02,938
You caught me a bit unprepared. We've
only got cold chicken and a bit of pickle...

190
00:17:03,104 --> 00:17:06,441
There's some cheese here.
No, that won't do.

191
00:17:06,691 --> 00:17:10,612
We've got raspberry jam,
an apple tart...

192
00:17:11,279 --> 00:17:15,242
But not much for afters.
Oh, no, we're all right.

193
00:17:15,450 --> 00:17:18,286
I've just found some sponge cake.

194
00:17:21,206 --> 00:17:22,541
I could make you some eggs
if you'd--

195
00:17:26,294 --> 00:17:28,964
- Just tea, thank you.
- Oh, right.

196
00:17:30,131 --> 00:17:32,467
- You don't mind if I eat, do you?
- No, not at all.

197
00:17:32,634 --> 00:17:33,969
[KNOCKING]

198
00:17:34,177 --> 00:17:35,428
FEMALE HOBBIT:
Bilbo! Bilbo Baggins!

199
00:17:35,637 --> 00:17:37,222
I'm not at home!

200
00:17:43,228 --> 00:17:45,814
It's the Sackville-Bagginses.

201
00:17:45,981 --> 00:17:48,108
- I know you're in there!
- They're after the house.

202
00:17:48,775 --> 00:17:51,278
They've never forgiven me
for living this long.

203
00:17:51,486 --> 00:17:54,281
I've got to get away from these confounded
relatives, hanging on the be” all day...

204
00:17:54,447 --> 00:17:56,324
...never giving me a moment's peace.

205
00:17:57,117 --> 00:18:00,662
I want to see mountains again.
Mountains, Gandalf!

206
00:18:00,829 --> 00:18:05,333
And then find somewhere quiet
where I can finish my book. Oh, tea.

207
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:09,504
- So you mean to go through with your plan?
- Yes, yes. It's all in hand.

208
00:18:09,671 --> 00:18:11,965
All the arrangements are made.

209
00:18:14,009 --> 00:18:15,510
Oh, thank you.

210
00:18:16,261 --> 00:18:18,346
Frodo suspects something.

211
00:18:18,513 --> 00:18:21,016
Of course he does. He's a Baggins...

212
00:18:21,266 --> 00:18:23,852
...not some block headed Bracegirdle
from Hardbottle.

213
00:18:24,352 --> 00:18:27,188
You will tell him, won't you?

214
00:18:28,023 --> 00:18:30,150
- Yes, yes.
- He's very fond of you.

215
00:18:32,360 --> 00:18:33,862
I know.

216
00:18:36,197 --> 00:18:39,534
He'd probably come with me
if I asked him.

217
00:18:40,201 --> 00:18:43,663
I think in his heart, Frodo's
still in love with the Shire.

218
00:18:45,206 --> 00:18:47,542
The woods, the fields.

219
00:18:47,709 --> 00:18:50,045
Little rivers.

220
00:18:54,549 --> 00:18:57,218
I am old, Gandalf.

221
00:18:58,553 --> 00:19:03,892
I know I don't look it, but I'm
beginning to feel it in my heart.

222
00:19:06,061 --> 00:19:08,563
I feel thin.

223
00:19:08,730 --> 00:19:10,398
Sort of stretched...

224
00:19:11,733 --> 00:19:15,070
...like butter scraped
over too much bread.

225
00:19:15,236 --> 00:19:19,741
I need a holiday. A very long holiday.

226
00:19:19,908 --> 00:19:23,203
And I don't expect I shall return.

227
00:19:25,413 --> 00:19:28,583
In fact, I mean not to.

228
00:19:31,252 --> 00:19:35,382
Old Toby. The finest weed
in the South far thing.

229
00:19:50,105 --> 00:19:51,731
Ah.

230
00:19:52,732 --> 00:19:55,276
Gandalf, my old friend...

231
00:19:55,443 --> 00:19:58,279
...this will be a night to remember.

232
00:19:59,864 --> 00:20:01,825
[CHEERING]

233
00:20:03,034 --> 00:20:06,121
[MUSIC PLAYS]

234
00:20:21,136 --> 00:20:22,137
BILBO:
Hello, hello.

235
00:20:22,470 --> 00:20:26,474
Fatty Bolger. Lovely to see you.
Welcome, welcome.

236
00:20:27,475 --> 00:20:30,103
Go on, Sam. Ask Rosie for a dance.

237
00:20:32,647 --> 00:20:36,276
- I think I'll just have another ale.
- Oh, no, you don't.

238
00:20:37,318 --> 00:20:39,112
Go on!

239
00:20:49,164 --> 00:20:50,999
So there I was...

240
00:20:51,291 --> 00:20:55,336
...at the mercy
of three monstrous trolls.

241
00:20:55,503 --> 00:20:57,505
And they were all arguing
amongst themselves...

242
00:20:57,672 --> 00:21:00,133
...about how they were
going to cook us.

243
00:21:00,341 --> 00:21:05,346
Whether it be turned on a spit, or to sit
on us one by one, squash us into jelly.

244
00:21:06,347 --> 00:21:09,934
They spent so much time arguing
the whithertos and the whyfors...

245
00:21:10,143 --> 00:21:13,688
...that the sun's first light
crept over the top of the trees...

246
00:21:14,689 --> 00:21:17,192
...and turned them all to stone!

247
00:21:18,276 --> 00:21:20,361
[LAUGHS]

248
00:21:22,489 --> 00:21:23,865
MERRY:
Quickly.

249
00:21:26,326 --> 00:21:27,827
Whoa!

250
00:21:28,036 --> 00:21:30,038
Up they go!

251
00:21:32,999 --> 00:21:34,209
No, the big one.

252
00:21:43,384 --> 00:21:46,221
Mrs. Bracegirdle, how nice to see you.
Welcome, welcome.

253
00:21:46,387 --> 00:21:48,348
Are all these children yours?

254
00:21:48,515 --> 00:21:51,518
Good gracious,
you have been productive.

255
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:54,854
FEMALE HOBBIT:
Bilbo?

256
00:21:56,564 --> 00:21:58,233
Sackville-Bagginses!

257
00:21:58,483 --> 00:21:59,567
Quickly, hide!

258
00:22:09,410 --> 00:22:11,579
Thank you, my boy.

259
00:22:13,081 --> 00:22:15,500
You're a good lad, Frodo.

260
00:22:16,709 --> 00:22:19,587
I'm very selfish, you know.

261
00:22:20,004 --> 00:22:23,424
Yes, I am. Very selfish.

262
00:22:23,591 --> 00:22:25,844
I don't know why I took you in
after your mother and father died...

263
00:22:26,010 --> 00:22:27,554
...but it wasn't out of charity.

264
00:22:28,263 --> 00:22:29,722
I think it was because...

265
00:22:29,889 --> 00:22:32,225
...of all my numerous relations...

266
00:22:32,517 --> 00:22:36,020
...you were the one Baggins
that showed real spirit.

267
00:22:36,271 --> 00:22:38,106
Bilbo, have you been
at the Gaffer's home brew?

268
00:22:38,273 --> 00:22:40,024
No.

269
00:22:40,275 --> 00:22:42,944
Well, yes, but that's not the point.

270
00:22:43,111 --> 00:22:46,406
The point is, Frodo...

271
00:22:49,450 --> 00:22:51,452
...you'll be all right.

272
00:22:54,789 --> 00:22:56,958
- Done!
- You're supposed to stick it in the ground.

273
00:22:57,125 --> 00:22:58,626
- It is in the ground.
- Outside!

274
00:22:58,793 --> 00:23:00,295
This was your idea.

275
00:23:16,144 --> 00:23:17,645
Bilbo.

276
00:23:18,813 --> 00:23:21,649
Bilbo, watch out for the dragon!

277
00:23:21,816 --> 00:23:25,153
Nonsense. There hasn't been a dragon
in these parts for a thousand years.

278
00:23:38,666 --> 00:23:42,337
- That was good.
- Let's get another one.

279
00:23:43,546 --> 00:23:48,092
GANDALF:
Meriadoc Brandybuck and Peregrin Took.

280
00:23:48,259 --> 00:23:50,136
I might've known.

281
00:23:56,017 --> 00:23:58,102
FEMALE HOBBIT:
Speech, Bilbo!

282
00:23:58,978 --> 00:24:00,313
MALE HOBBIT:
Speech!

283
00:24:00,521 --> 00:24:01,606
Speech!

284
00:24:06,861 --> 00:24:09,155
My dear Bagginses and Boffins...

285
00:24:09,948 --> 00:24:12,158
...Tooks and Brandybucks...

286
00:24:12,325 --> 00:24:14,827
...Grubbs, Chubbs...

287
00:24:15,036 --> 00:24:16,079
...Hornb|owers...

288
00:24:17,205 --> 00:24:18,873
...Bo|gers...

289
00:24:19,290 --> 00:24:20,833
...Bracegird|es...

290
00:24:21,042 --> 00:24:23,670
- ...and Proudfoots.
- Proudfeet!

291
00:24:25,838 --> 00:24:29,008
Today is my 111th birthday!

292
00:24:30,802 --> 00:24:32,345
Happy birthday!

293
00:24:32,553 --> 00:24:36,849
But alas, eleventy-one years is
far too short a time to live among...

294
00:24:37,016 --> 00:24:39,894
...such excellent
and admirable Hobbits.

295
00:24:40,853 --> 00:24:43,564
I don't know half of you
half as well as I should like...

296
00:24:43,731 --> 00:24:48,361
...and I like less than half of you
half as well as you deserve.

297
00:24:51,864 --> 00:24:53,491
I, uh——

298
00:24:58,329 --> 00:25:00,707
I have things to do.

299
00:25:07,088 --> 00:25:09,215
I've put this off far too long.

300
00:25:13,052 --> 00:25:17,015
I regret to announce this is the end!

301
00:25:18,182 --> 00:25:19,350
I'm going now.

302
00:25:20,435 --> 00:25:23,354
I bid you all a very fond farewell.

303
00:25:25,732 --> 00:25:26,941
Goodbye.

304
00:25:32,780 --> 00:25:34,449
[HOBBITS CLAMORING]

305
00:25:36,617 --> 00:25:39,287
[FOOTSTEPS]

306
00:25:50,131 --> 00:25:52,216
[LAUGHS]

307
00:26:00,183 --> 00:26:03,311
I suppose you think
that was terribly clever.

308
00:26:03,478 --> 00:26:06,898
Come on, Gandalf.
Did you see their faces?

309
00:26:07,065 --> 00:26:12,111
There are many magic rings in this world,
and none of them should be used lightly.

310
00:26:12,320 --> 00:26:14,489
It was just a bit of fun.

311
00:26:14,697 --> 00:26:18,409
Oh, you're probably right, as usual.

312
00:26:19,786 --> 00:26:23,331
- You will keep an eye on Frodo, won't you?
- Two eyes.

313
00:26:23,498 --> 00:26:26,209
As often as I can spare them.

314
00:26:26,417 --> 00:26:29,587
- I'm leaving everything to him.
- What about this ring of yours?

315
00:26:29,796 --> 00:26:33,132
- Is that staying too?
- Yes, yes.

316
00:26:33,758 --> 00:26:37,637
It's in an envelope over there
on the mantelpiece.

317
00:26:38,721 --> 00:26:41,682
No. Wait, it's...

318
00:26:44,185 --> 00:26:46,854
...here in my pocket.

319
00:26:51,359 --> 00:26:54,737
Isn't that--? Isn't that odd, now?

320
00:26:56,364 --> 00:26:59,867
Yet, after all, why not?

321
00:27:01,452 --> 00:27:06,332
- Why shouldn't I keep it?
- I think you should leave the ring behind.

322
00:27:06,749 --> 00:27:08,960
Is that so hard?

323
00:27:09,127 --> 00:27:10,461
Well, no.

324
00:27:12,839 --> 00:27:14,382
And yes.

325
00:27:16,342 --> 00:27:19,387
Now it comes to it,
I don't feel like parting with it.

326
00:27:19,637 --> 00:27:21,389
It's mine. I found it! It came to me!

327
00:27:21,556 --> 00:27:25,810
- There's no need to get angry.
- Well, if I'm angry, it's your fault!

328
00:27:26,269 --> 00:27:28,062
It's mine.

329
00:27:29,313 --> 00:27:31,816
My own.

330
00:27:32,150 --> 00:27:36,154
- My precious.
- Precious?

331
00:27:36,320 --> 00:27:39,198
It's been called that before,
but not by you.

332
00:27:39,407 --> 00:27:41,993
What business is it of yours
what I do with my own things?

333
00:27:42,201 --> 00:27:44,912
I think you've had that ring
quite long enough.

334
00:27:45,163 --> 00:27:47,999
- You want it for yourself!
- Bilbo Baggins!

335
00:27:48,207 --> 00:27:52,420
Do not take me for some conjurer
of cheap tricks.

336
00:27:52,670 --> 00:27:56,340
I am not trying to rob you.

337
00:28:01,387 --> 00:28:03,097
I'm trying to help you.

338
00:28:04,432 --> 00:28:05,975
[BILBO WHIMPERS]

339
00:28:11,564 --> 00:28:14,901
All your long years,
we've been friends.

340
00:28:15,276 --> 00:28:17,445
Trust me as you once did.

341
00:28:19,280 --> 00:28:21,115
Let it go.

342
00:28:22,241 --> 00:28:24,660
You're right, Gandalf.

343
00:28:26,787 --> 00:28:29,457
The ring must go to Frodo.

344
00:28:30,791 --> 00:28:33,794
It's late. The road is long.

345
00:28:33,961 --> 00:28:36,464
Yes, it is time.

346
00:28:39,300 --> 00:28:41,302
- Bilbo.
- Hm?

347
00:28:41,802 --> 00:28:44,305
The ring is still in your pocket.

348
00:28:46,682 --> 00:28:48,601
Ah. Yes.

349
00:29:19,006 --> 00:29:22,009
I've thought up an ending for my book:

350
00:29:23,678 --> 00:29:28,683
"And he lived happily ever after
to the end of his days."

351
00:29:28,849 --> 00:29:32,311
And I'm sure you will, my dear friend.

352
00:29:33,354 --> 00:29:34,814
Goodbye, Gandalf.

353
00:29:37,316 --> 00:29:40,194
Goodbye, dear Bilbo.

354
00:29:47,994 --> 00:29:52,206
<i>BILBO:
The road goes ever on and on</i>

355
00:29:54,750 --> 00:29:57,128
Until our next meeting.

356
00:30:24,530 --> 00:30:28,200
<i>BILBO:
It's mine. My own.</i>

357
00:30:28,367 --> 00:30:31,787
<i>My precious.</i>

358
00:30:32,079 --> 00:30:34,999
Riddles in the dark.

359
00:30:35,207 --> 00:30:36,625
Bilbo!

360
00:30:36,792 --> 00:30:38,377
Bilbo!

361
00:30:42,006 --> 00:30:44,925
My precious.

362
00:30:46,552 --> 00:30:48,763
Precious.

363
00:30:48,929 --> 00:30:51,515
He's gone, hasn't he?

364
00:30:54,268 --> 00:30:57,313
He talked for so long about leaving...

365
00:30:57,563 --> 00:31:00,274
...I didn't think he'd really do it.

366
00:31:04,737 --> 00:31:06,614
Gandalf?

367
00:31:14,914 --> 00:31:16,582
Bilbo's ring.

368
00:31:16,916 --> 00:31:19,293
He's gone to stay with the Elves.

369
00:31:19,460 --> 00:31:22,588
He's left you Bag End.

370
00:31:26,175 --> 00:31:28,761
Along with all his possessions.

371
00:31:28,928 --> 00:31:31,806
The ring is yours now.

372
00:31:34,433 --> 00:31:37,937
- Put it somewhere out of sight.
- Where are you going?

373
00:31:38,104 --> 00:31:40,356
- There are some things that I must see to.
- What things?

374
00:31:40,564 --> 00:31:44,819
—Questions. Questions that need answering.
- You've only just arrived.

375
00:31:45,694 --> 00:31:48,322
I don't understand.

376
00:31:51,659 --> 00:31:52,660
Neither do I.

377
00:31:55,955 --> 00:31:58,290
Keep it secret.

378
00:31:58,457 --> 00:32:00,209
Keep it safe.

379
00:32:32,616 --> 00:32:35,035
[GOLLUM SCREAMS]

380
00:32:35,202 --> 00:32:37,371
<i>GOLLUM:
Shire!</i>

381
00:32:37,705 --> 00:32:40,833
<i>Baggins!</i>

382
00:32:53,053 --> 00:32:55,639
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

383
00:33:29,381 --> 00:33:32,259
<i>GANDALF:
"The year 3434 of the Second Age.</i>

384
00:33:32,468 --> 00:33:36,889
<i>Here follows the account of lsildur,
High King of Gondor...</i>

385
00:33:37,097 --> 00:33:40,768
<i>...and the finding
of the Ring of Power."</i>

386
00:33:44,271 --> 00:33:46,106
<i>"It has come to me.</i>

387
00:33:46,273 --> 00:33:49,777
<i>The One Ring. It shall be
an heirloom of my kingdom.</i>

388
00:33:49,944 --> 00:33:53,405
<i>All those who follow in my bloodline
shall be bound to its fate...</i>

389
00:33:53,614 --> 00:33:57,409
<i>...for I will risk
no hurt to the Ring.</i>

390
00:33:57,618 --> 00:34:00,120
<i>It is precious to</i> me...

391
00:34:00,955 --> 00:34:03,624
<i>...though I buy it with great pain.</i>

392
00:34:06,752 --> 00:34:10,965
<i>The markings upon the band
begin to fade.</i>

393
00:34:11,298 --> 00:34:15,970
<i>The writing, which at first was as clear
as red flame, has all but disappeared.</i>

394
00:34:16,220 --> 00:34:20,266
<i>A secret now
that only fire can tell."</i>

395
00:34:24,812 --> 00:34:26,647
[HOOVES CLOPPING]

396
00:34:36,782 --> 00:34:39,785
Shire.

397
00:34:39,952 --> 00:34:41,954
Baggins.

398
00:34:42,454 --> 00:34:46,500
There's no Bagginses around here.
They're all up in Hobbiton.

399
00:34:48,168 --> 00:34:49,670
That way.

400
00:34:55,676 --> 00:34:57,886
<i>To heal my heart and drown my woe</i>

401
00:34:58,053 --> 00:35:00,389
<i>Rain may fall and wind may blow</i>

402
00:35:00,556 --> 00:35:02,516
<i>But there still be</i>

403
00:35:02,683 --> 00:35:04,143
<i>Many miles to go</i>

404
00:35:04,351 --> 00:35:06,270
<i>Sweet is the sound of the pouring rain</i>

405
00:35:06,478 --> 00:35:08,647
<i>And the stream that falls
From hill to plain</i>

406
00:35:08,856 --> 00:35:10,691
<i>Better than rain or rippling brook</i>

407
00:35:10,858 --> 00:35:13,277
<i>Is a mug of beer inside this Took</i>

408
00:35:16,697 --> 00:35:19,533
There's been some strange folk
crossing the Shire.

409
00:35:19,992 --> 00:35:23,829
Dwarves and others of a less
than savory nature.

410
00:35:24,330 --> 00:35:25,706
War is brewing.

411
00:35:26,373 --> 00:35:29,209
The mountains are fair teeming
with goblins.

412
00:35:29,418 --> 00:35:32,046
Far-off tales and children's stories,
that's all that is.

413
00:35:32,212 --> 00:35:36,717
You're beginning to sound like that old
Bilbo Baggins. Cracked, he was.

414
00:35:36,884 --> 00:35:39,887
Young Mr. Frodo here,
he's cracking.

415
00:35:40,054 --> 00:35:41,513
And proud of it.

416
00:35:41,680 --> 00:35:43,932
- Cheers, Gaffer.
- Cheers.

417
00:35:44,099 --> 00:35:48,228
It's none of our concern what goes on
beyond our borders.

418
00:35:48,395 --> 00:35:52,733
Keep your nose out of trouble,
and no trouble'll come to you.

419
00:35:56,070 --> 00:35:58,280
- Good night, lads.
- Good night.

420
00:35:58,447 --> 00:36:02,951
Good night, sweet maiden
of the golden ale.

421
00:36:03,118 --> 00:36:05,537
Mind who you're sweet-talking.

422
00:36:05,704 --> 00:36:10,250
Don't worry, <i>Sam.</i> Rosie knows an idiot
when she sees one.

423
00:36:11,251 --> 00:36:12,419
Does she?

424
00:36:13,087 --> 00:36:16,090
- Good night, <i>Sam.</i>
- Good night, Mr. Frodo.

425
00:36:40,864 --> 00:36:43,367
Is it secret? Is it safe?

426
00:36:45,953 --> 00:36:47,871
[PIG SQUEALS]

427
00:36:49,123 --> 00:36:50,582
Ah.

428
00:36:52,251 --> 00:36:54,378
What are you doing?

429
00:37:06,974 --> 00:37:09,476
Hold out your hand, Frodo.

430
00:37:09,643 --> 00:37:10,811
It's quite cool.

431
00:37:14,398 --> 00:37:16,150
What can you see?

432
00:37:17,985 --> 00:37:20,320
Can you see anything?

433
00:37:23,031 --> 00:37:24,491
Nothing.

434
00:37:25,117 --> 00:37:27,119
There's nothing.

435
00:37:28,162 --> 00:37:29,663
Wait.

436
00:37:33,792 --> 00:37:36,003
There are markings.

437
00:37:37,504 --> 00:37:40,924
It's some form of Elvish.
I can't read it.

438
00:37:41,133 --> 00:37:43,677
There are few who can.

439
00:37:44,219 --> 00:37:49,057
The language is that of Mordor,
which I will not utter here.

440
00:37:49,683 --> 00:37:50,726
Mordor!

441
00:37:51,018 --> 00:37:53,020
In the common tongue, it says:

442
00:37:53,228 --> 00:37:56,732
"One Ring to rule them all...

443
00:37:57,024 --> 00:37:59,318
...One Ring to find them...

444
00:37:59,526 --> 00:38:01,695
...One Ring to bring them all...

445
00:38:02,029 --> 00:38:05,032
...and in the darkness bind them."

446
00:38:06,658 --> 00:38:08,702
This is the One Ring...

447
00:38:08,869 --> 00:38:14,166
...forged by the Dark Lord Sauron
in the fires of Mount Doom.

448
00:38:14,374 --> 00:38:18,378
Taken by lsildur
from the hand of Sauron himself.

449
00:38:19,171 --> 00:38:21,715
Bilbo found it.

450
00:38:22,174 --> 00:38:24,092
- In Gollum's cave.
- Yes.

451
00:38:24,343 --> 00:38:28,889
For 60 years, the Ring lay quiet
in Bilbo's keeping...

452
00:38:29,056 --> 00:38:32,476
...prolonging his life,
delaying old age.

453
00:38:33,101 --> 00:38:37,564
But no longer, Frodo.
Evil is stirring in Mordor.

454
00:38:37,731 --> 00:38:40,108
The Ring has awoken.

455
00:38:40,359 --> 00:38:43,070
It's heard its master's call.

456
00:38:43,278 --> 00:38:47,199
But he was destroyed.
Sauron was destroyed.

457
00:38:48,408 --> 00:38:50,577
[VOICE OF THE RING
WHISPERS IN BLACK SPEECH]

458
00:38:52,913 --> 00:38:54,998
GANDALF:
No, Frodo.

459
00:38:55,916 --> 00:38:59,253
The spirit of Sauron endured.

460
00:38:59,419 --> 00:39:04,758
His life force is bound to the Ring,
and the Ring survived.

461
00:39:05,092 --> 00:39:07,261
Sauron has returned.

462
00:39:08,136 --> 00:39:10,264
His Orcs have multiplied.

463
00:39:10,430 --> 00:39:14,476
His fortress at Barad-dflr
is rebuilt in the land of Mordor.

464
00:39:14,643 --> 00:39:19,439
Sauron needs only this Ring to cover
all the lands in a second darkness.

465
00:39:19,648 --> 00:39:21,733
He is seeking it.

466
00:39:21,942 --> 00:39:25,779
Seeking it. All his thought
is bent on it.

467
00:39:26,029 --> 00:39:28,740
For the Ring yearns above all else...

468
00:39:28,949 --> 00:39:32,327
...to return to the hand
of its master.

469
00:39:32,619 --> 00:39:34,329
They are one...

470
00:39:34,538 --> 00:39:37,624
...the Ring and the Dark Lord.

471
00:39:37,791 --> 00:39:38,834
Frodo...

472
00:39:39,418 --> 00:39:41,295
...he must never find it.

473
00:39:41,461 --> 00:39:42,546
FRODO:
All right.

474
00:39:42,838 --> 00:39:47,175
We put it away. We keep it hidden.
We never speak of it again.

475
00:39:47,342 --> 00:39:50,053
No one knows it's here, do they?

476
00:39:55,684 --> 00:39:56,935
Do they, Gandalf?

477
00:39:57,978 --> 00:40:01,356
There is one other who knew
that Bilbo had the Ring.

478
00:40:02,649 --> 00:40:05,652
I looked everywhere
for the creature GOLLUM.

479
00:40:05,819 --> 00:40:07,988
But the enemy found him first.

480
00:40:08,196 --> 00:40:09,531
[GOLLUM SCREAMS]

481
00:40:09,698 --> 00:40:12,200
<i>GANDALF: I don't know how long
they tortured him.</i>

482
00:40:12,367 --> 00:40:16,872
<i>But a midst the endless screams and
inane babble, they discerned two words:</i>

483
00:40:17,080 --> 00:40:19,207
GOLLUM:
Shire!

484
00:40:19,374 --> 00:40:21,001
Baggins!

485
00:40:21,209 --> 00:40:23,045
Shire.

486
00:40:23,211 --> 00:40:26,173
Baggins. But that would
lead them here!

487
00:40:28,842 --> 00:40:30,010
Who goes there?

488
00:40:31,720 --> 00:40:32,971
Take it, Gandalf!

489
00:40:33,347 --> 00:40:34,389
- Take it!
- No, Frodo.

490
00:40:34,598 --> 00:40:36,975
- You must take it!
- You cannot offer me this ring!

491
00:40:37,184 --> 00:40:40,520
- I'm giving it to you!
- Don't tempt me, Frodo!

492
00:40:42,022 --> 00:40:44,232
I dare not take it.

493
00:40:44,608 --> 00:40:47,027
Not even to keep it safe.

494
00:40:48,195 --> 00:40:50,197
Understand, Frodo...

495
00:40:50,864 --> 00:40:54,493
...I would use this Ring
from a desire to do good.

496
00:40:59,873 --> 00:41:05,629
But through me, it would wield a power
too great and terrible to imagine.

497
00:41:06,213 --> 00:41:09,132
- But it cannot stay in the Shire!
- No.

498
00:41:11,009 --> 00:41:12,636
No, it can't.

499
00:41:17,933 --> 00:41:19,351
What must I do?

500
00:41:21,019 --> 00:41:24,564
- You must leave. And leave quickly.
- Where? Where do I go?

501
00:41:24,731 --> 00:41:28,026
Get out of the Shire.
Make for the village of Bree.

502
00:41:28,276 --> 00:41:29,403
Bree.

503
00:41:29,569 --> 00:41:32,364
- What about you?
- I'll be waiting for you...

504
00:41:32,572 --> 00:41:35,033
...at the inn of the Prancing Pony.

505
00:41:35,242 --> 00:41:38,954
- And the Ring will be safe there?
- I don't know, Frodo.

506
00:41:39,162 --> 00:41:41,164
I don't have any answers.

507
00:41:42,666 --> 00:41:48,255
I must see the head of my order. He is
both wise and powerful. Trust me, Frodo.

508
00:41:48,422 --> 00:41:50,549
He'll know what to do.

509
00:41:51,174 --> 00:41:53,969
You'll have to leave the name
of Baggins behind you.

510
00:41:54,261 --> 00:41:56,763
That name is not safe
outside the Shire.

511
00:41:57,389 --> 00:42:00,684
Travel only by day.
And stay off the road.

512
00:42:01,309 --> 00:42:04,479
I can cut across country
easily enough.

513
00:42:06,982 --> 00:42:08,316
My dear Frodo.

514
00:42:08,608 --> 00:42:11,653
Hobbits really are amazing creatures.

515
00:42:11,820 --> 00:42:14,781
You can learn all that there is to
know about their ways in a month.

516
00:42:14,948 --> 00:42:17,325
And yet, after a hundred years...

517
00:42:17,492 --> 00:42:19,578
...they can still surprise you.

518
00:42:19,786 --> 00:42:20,954
[RUSTLING]

519
00:42:21,204 --> 00:42:22,497
Get down.

520
00:42:31,131 --> 00:42:32,257
[GROANING]

521
00:42:34,801 --> 00:42:38,263
Confound it all, Samwise Gamgee!
Have you been eavesdropping?

522
00:42:38,430 --> 00:42:42,934
I haven't been dropping no eaves. Honest.
I was cutting the grass under the window.

523
00:42:43,101 --> 00:42:45,520
A little late for trimming the verge,
don't you think?

524
00:42:45,729 --> 00:42:48,607
- I heard raised voices.
- What did you hear? Speak!

525
00:42:48,815 --> 00:42:49,858
Nothing important.

526
00:42:50,442 --> 00:42:54,529
That is, I heard a good deal about a ring,
a Dark Lord and the end of the world but--

527
00:42:54,738 --> 00:42:59,493
Please, Mr. Gandalf, sir, don't hurt me.
Don't turn me into anything unnatural.

528
00:43:00,160 --> 00:43:01,828
No?

529
00:43:02,996 --> 00:43:04,164
Perhaps not.

530
00:43:05,373 --> 00:43:08,835
I've thought of a better use for you.

531
00:43:10,545 --> 00:43:13,548
GANDALF:
Come along, Samwise. Keep up.

532
00:43:15,050 --> 00:43:17,344
Be careful, both of you.

533
00:43:17,552 --> 00:43:20,347
The enemy has many spies
in his service:

534
00:43:20,555 --> 00:43:23,517
Birds, beasts.

535
00:43:25,268 --> 00:43:27,062
Is it safe?

536
00:43:28,772 --> 00:43:30,148
Never put it on...

537
00:43:30,357 --> 00:43:33,735
...for the agents of the Dark Lord
will be drawn to its power.

538
00:43:33,902 --> 00:43:35,403
Always remember, Frodo...

539
00:43:35,904 --> 00:43:39,074
...the Ring is trying to get back
to its master.

540
00:43:39,491 --> 00:43:41,576
It wants to be found.

541
00:43:49,042 --> 00:43:51,795
[BIRDS SQUAWKING]

542
00:44:22,200 --> 00:44:24,411
This is it.

543
00:44:24,744 --> 00:44:26,913
This is what?

544
00:44:27,205 --> 00:44:29,249
If I take one more step...

545
00:44:29,749 --> 00:44:33,628
...it'll be the farthest away
from home I've ever been.

546
00:44:37,924 --> 00:44:39,426
Come on, <i>Sam.</i>

547
00:44:47,851 --> 00:44:49,644
Remember what Bilbo used to say:

548
00:44:50,228 --> 00:44:53,982
-"It's a dangerous business, <i>Frodo."</i>
BILBO: <i>"Going out your door.</i>

549
00:44:54,149 --> 00:44:58,612
<i>You step onto the road,
and if you don't keep your feet...</i>

550
00:44:58,778 --> 00:45:02,949
<i>...there's no knowing where
you might be swept off to."</i>

551
00:45:11,583 --> 00:45:13,960
[SINGING]

552
00:45:16,963 --> 00:45:18,798
<i>Sam.</i>

553
00:45:22,302 --> 00:45:23,428
Wood-elves.

554
00:45:37,150 --> 00:45:40,654
They're going to the harbor
beyond the White Towers.

555
00:45:41,196 --> 00:45:42,989
To the Grey Havens.

556
00:45:43,573 --> 00:45:45,617
SAM:
They're leaving Middle-earth.

557
00:45:45,784 --> 00:45:47,994
FRODO:
Never to return.

558
00:45:50,872 --> 00:45:52,999
I don't know why...

559
00:45:53,667 --> 00:45:56,086
...it makes me sad.

560
00:45:58,171 --> 00:46:02,801
Everywhere I lie there's a dirty
great root sticking into my back.

561
00:46:03,510 --> 00:46:05,220
Just shut your eyes...

562
00:46:05,387 --> 00:46:08,181
...and imagine you're back
in your own bed...

563
00:46:08,348 --> 00:46:12,310
...with a soft mattress
and a lovely feather pillow.

564
00:46:21,611 --> 00:46:24,322
It's not working, Mr. Frodo.

565
00:46:24,489 --> 00:46:27,367
I'm never going to be able
to sleep out here.

566
00:46:29,703 --> 00:46:32,038
Me neither, Sam.

567
00:47:00,567 --> 00:47:03,611
MALE VOICE: <i>Smoke rises
from the Mountain of Doom.</i>

568
00:47:03,778 --> 00:47:05,447
<i>The hour grows late.</i>

569
00:47:05,655 --> 00:47:09,242
<i>And Gandalf the Grey
rides to lsengard...</i>

570
00:47:09,409 --> 00:47:11,870
<i>...seeking my counsel.</i>

571
00:47:12,078 --> 00:47:16,082
For that is why you have come,
is it not?

572
00:47:16,249 --> 00:47:17,542
My old friend.

573
00:47:17,792 --> 00:47:19,419
Saruman.

574
00:47:24,215 --> 00:47:27,260
SARUMAN: You are sure of this?
GANDALF: Beyond any doubt.

575
00:47:28,053 --> 00:47:30,305
So the Ring of Power has been found.

576
00:47:30,472 --> 00:47:33,725
All these long years,
it was in the Shire.

577
00:47:33,892 --> 00:47:37,062
- Under my very nose.
- Yet you did not have the wit to see it.

578
00:47:37,687 --> 00:47:42,192
Your love of the half ling's leaf
has clearly slowed your mind.

579
00:47:43,068 --> 00:47:47,072
But we still have time. Time enough
to counter Sauron if we act quickly.

580
00:47:47,238 --> 00:47:48,698
Time?

581
00:47:49,616 --> 00:47:52,243
What time do you think we have?

582
00:47:52,702 --> 00:47:56,581
Sauron has regained
much of his former strength.

583
00:47:56,748 --> 00:47:58,958
He cannot yet take physical form...

584
00:47:59,209 --> 00:48:01,920
...but his spirit has lost
none of its potency.

585
00:48:02,587 --> 00:48:07,634
Concealed within his fortress,
the Lord of Mordor sees all.

586
00:48:08,218 --> 00:48:14,140
His gaze pierces cloud, shadow,
earth and flesh.

587
00:48:15,642 --> 00:48:18,812
You know of what I speak, Gandalf.

588
00:48:19,729 --> 00:48:24,984
A Great Eye, lidless,
wreathed in flame.

589
00:48:25,944 --> 00:48:27,737
The Eye of Sauron.

590
00:48:27,946 --> 00:48:30,532
He is gathering all evil to him.

591
00:48:30,740 --> 00:48:33,243
Very soon, he'll have summoned
an army great enough...

592
00:48:33,410 --> 00:48:35,620
...for an assault upon Middle-earth.

593
00:48:35,954 --> 00:48:38,331
You know this?

594
00:48:38,832 --> 00:48:40,333
How?

595
00:48:40,959 --> 00:48:42,627
I have seen it.

596
00:48:43,044 --> 00:48:46,256
A palantir is a dangerous tool,
Saruman.

597
00:48:46,965 --> 00:48:48,466
Why?

598
00:48:48,925 --> 00:48:51,636
Why should we fear to use it?

599
00:48:54,264 --> 00:48:58,184
They are not all accounted for,
the lost Seeing-stones.

600
00:48:58,351 --> 00:49:01,604
We do not know who else
may be watching.

601
00:49:04,190 --> 00:49:06,943
The hour is later than you think.

602
00:49:07,110 --> 00:49:09,446
Sauron's forces are already moving.

603
00:49:11,698 --> 00:49:14,451
The Nine have left Minas Morgul.

604
00:49:14,826 --> 00:49:15,869
The Nine?

605
00:49:16,035 --> 00:49:19,122
They crossed the River Isen
on Midsummer's Eve...

606
00:49:19,289 --> 00:49:21,958
...disguised as riders in black.

607
00:49:22,167 --> 00:49:26,129
- They've reached the Shire?
- They will find the Ring.

608
00:49:27,714 --> 00:49:29,966
And kill the one who carries it.

609
00:49:30,467 --> 00:49:31,968
Frodo!

610
00:49:44,564 --> 00:49:48,985
You did not seriously think that a Hobbit
could contend with the will of Sauron?

611
00:49:49,736 --> 00:49:52,530
There are none who can.

612
00:49:55,033 --> 00:49:57,744
Against the power of Mordor...

613
00:49:57,911 --> 00:50:00,580
...there can be no victory.

614
00:50:02,540 --> 00:50:05,710
We must join with him, Gandalf.

615
00:50:07,003 --> 00:50:09,339
We must join with Sauron.

616
00:50:12,008 --> 00:50:14,677
It would be wise, my friend.

617
00:50:15,136 --> 00:50:16,596
Tell me...

618
00:50:16,763 --> 00:50:17,847
...friend...

619
00:50:18,848 --> 00:50:23,394
...when did Saruman the Wise
abandon reason for madness?

620
00:51:02,892 --> 00:51:04,602
I gave you the chance...

621
00:51:05,728 --> 00:51:08,398
...of aiding me willingly...

622
00:51:08,565 --> 00:51:12,735
...but you have elected
the way of pain!

623
00:51:36,009 --> 00:51:37,510
SAM:
Mr. Frodo?

624
00:51:38,136 --> 00:51:39,929
Frodo? Frodo!

625
00:51:41,347 --> 00:51:44,601
- I thought I'd lost you.
- What are you talking about?

626
00:51:44,767 --> 00:51:47,770
- It's just something Gandalf said.
- What did he say?

627
00:51:48,605 --> 00:51:52,483
"Don't you lose him, Samwise Gamgee."
And I don't mean to.

628
00:51:52,734 --> 00:51:56,362
Sam, we're still in the Shire.
What could possibly happen?

629
00:51:59,324 --> 00:52:00,366
Frodo.

630
00:52:00,617 --> 00:52:02,869
- Merry, it's Frodo Baggins.
- Hello, Frodo.

631
00:52:03,036 --> 00:52:04,454
Get off him.

632
00:52:04,954 --> 00:52:06,456
Come on, Frodo.

633
00:52:06,623 --> 00:52:08,499
FRODO:
What's the meaning of this?

634
00:52:08,958 --> 00:52:10,710
You've been into Farmer Maggot's crop!

635
00:52:10,960 --> 00:52:12,128
[DOG BARKS]

636
00:52:13,212 --> 00:52:15,340
MAGGOT:
You get back here!

637
00:52:16,341 --> 00:52:17,675
Get out of my field!

638
00:52:17,842 --> 00:52:20,678
You'll know the devil
if I catch up with you!

639
00:52:20,887 --> 00:52:23,848
MERRY: I don't know why he's so upset.
It's only a couple of carrots.

640
00:52:24,015 --> 00:52:25,141
PIPPIN:
And some cabbages.

641
00:52:25,308 --> 00:52:28,227
And those three bags of potatoes
that we lifted last week.

642
00:52:28,394 --> 00:52:32,482
-And then the mushrooms the week before.
MERRY: Yes, Pippin. My point is...

643
00:52:32,690 --> 00:52:34,859
...he's clearly overreacting.

644
00:52:35,068 --> 00:52:36,569
Run!

645
00:52:50,041 --> 00:52:52,585
Oh, that was close.

646
00:52:53,670 --> 00:52:56,798
I think I've broken something.

647
00:52:57,799 --> 00:53:00,176
Trust a Brandybuck and a Took!

648
00:53:00,343 --> 00:53:04,013
What? That was just a detour.
A short cut.

649
00:53:04,180 --> 00:53:06,432
- Short cut to what?
- Mushrooms!

650
00:53:15,191 --> 00:53:16,693
PIPPIN:
That's mine.

651
00:53:19,445 --> 00:53:21,072
That's nice, Merry.

652
00:53:21,614 --> 00:53:23,616
MERRY:
Here's a nice one, <i>Sam.</i>

653
00:53:23,825 --> 00:53:26,369
I think we should get off the road.

654
00:53:27,954 --> 00:53:31,624
[SCREECHING]

655
00:53:35,545 --> 00:53:36,921
Get off the road!

656
00:53:37,130 --> 00:53:38,631
Quick!

657
00:53:46,973 --> 00:53:51,060
[HOOVES CLOPPING]

658
00:53:51,310 --> 00:53:52,812
Be quiet!

659
00:54:19,922 --> 00:54:21,674
[SNIFFS]

660
00:54:59,128 --> 00:55:01,297
What was that?

661
00:55:20,566 --> 00:55:22,693
[SCREECHES]

662
00:55:33,996 --> 00:55:35,498
SAM:
Anything?

663
00:55:36,165 --> 00:55:37,667
Nothing.

664
00:55:38,376 --> 00:55:40,670
What is going on?

665
00:55:41,212 --> 00:55:45,007
That Black Rider was looking
for something. Or someone.

666
00:55:46,342 --> 00:55:47,844
Frodo?

667
00:55:48,553 --> 00:55:49,595
Get down!

668
00:56:06,529 --> 00:56:08,781
I have to leave the Shire.

669
00:56:09,782 --> 00:56:12,076
Sam and I must get to Bree.

670
00:56:12,285 --> 00:56:13,703
Right.

671
00:56:15,079 --> 00:56:17,373
Bucklebury Ferry. Follow me.

672
00:56:25,631 --> 00:56:27,008
PIPPIN:
Run!

673
00:56:28,217 --> 00:56:30,219
MERRY:
This way! Follow me!

674
00:56:33,764 --> 00:56:34,807
PIPPIN:
Run!

675
00:56:48,070 --> 00:56:49,822
MERRY:
Get the rope, Sam!

676
00:56:52,491 --> 00:56:54,035
Frodo!

677
00:56:54,744 --> 00:56:56,162
PIPPIN:
Run, Frodo!

678
00:56:56,495 --> 00:56:57,580
FRODO: Go!
PIPPIN: Hurry!

679
00:56:57,788 --> 00:57:00,416
MERRY:
Frodo, come on!

680
00:57:01,334 --> 00:57:03,336
SAM: Come on! Faster!
PIPPIN: Jump!

681
00:57:10,301 --> 00:57:11,802
[SCREECHES]

682
00:57:18,309 --> 00:57:22,521
- How far to the nearest crossing?
- The Brandywine Bridge. 20 miles.

683
00:57:37,119 --> 00:57:38,621
Come on.

684
00:57:49,799 --> 00:57:53,219
- What do you want?
- We're heading for the Prancing Pony.

685
00:57:56,722 --> 00:57:59,558
Hobbits. Four Hobbits!

686
00:57:59,725 --> 00:58:03,688
What's more, out of the Shire by your
talk. What business brings you to Bree?

687
00:58:04,105 --> 00:58:07,233
We wish to stay at the inn.
Our business is our own.

688
00:58:08,234 --> 00:58:10,820
All right, young sir.
I meant no offense.

689
00:58:10,987 --> 00:58:13,531
It's my job to ask questions
after nightfall.

690
00:58:13,698 --> 00:58:16,534
There's talk of strange folk abroad.

691
00:58:16,701 --> 00:58:18,869
Can't be too careful.

692
00:58:38,597 --> 00:58:42,101
Out of the way!
Watch where you're walking.

693
00:58:49,442 --> 00:58:52,153
[LAUGHING]

694
00:59:06,250 --> 00:59:07,877
Excuse me.

695
00:59:08,878 --> 00:59:11,714
Good evening, little masters.
What can I do for you?

696
00:59:11,881 --> 00:59:17,970
If you're seeking accommodation, we got
some cozy Hobbit-sized rooms available.

697
00:59:18,179 --> 00:59:22,808
Always proud to cater
to the Little Folk, Mister...?

698
00:59:23,976 --> 00:59:26,020
Underhill. My name's Underhill.

699
00:59:27,313 --> 00:59:29,815
- Underhi||, yes.
- We're friends of Gandalf the Grey.

700
00:59:29,982 --> 00:59:33,152
- Can you tell him we've arrived?
- Gandalf?

701
00:59:33,569 --> 00:59:35,321
Gandalf.

702
00:59:36,155 --> 00:59:37,823
Oh, yes...

703
00:59:38,032 --> 00:59:40,159
...I remember. Elderly chap.

704
00:59:40,493 --> 00:59:43,412
Big grey beard, pointy hat.

705
00:59:43,829 --> 00:59:45,664
Not seen him for six months.

706
00:59:52,421 --> 00:59:53,714
What do we do now?

707
01:00:00,930 --> 01:00:02,181
Sam...

708
01:00:02,348 --> 01:00:04,225
...he'll be here. He'll come.

709
01:00:07,019 --> 01:00:09,063
MAN:
Get out of my way!

710
01:00:11,440 --> 01:00:13,109
What's that?

711
01:00:13,359 --> 01:00:15,861
This, my friend, is a pint.

712
01:00:16,028 --> 01:00:17,696
It comes in pints?

713
01:00:18,030 --> 01:00:21,742
- I'm getting one.
- You got a whole half already!

714
01:00:28,082 --> 01:00:31,919
That fellow's done nothing
but stare at you since we arrived.

715
01:00:35,464 --> 01:00:36,966
Excuse me.

716
01:00:38,759 --> 01:00:41,762
That Man in the corner. Who is he?

717
01:00:42,930 --> 01:00:47,351
He's one of them Rangers. They're
dangerous folk, wandering the Wilds.

718
01:00:47,601 --> 01:00:52,106
What his right name is, I've never heard,
but around here he's known as Strider.

719
01:00:54,483 --> 01:00:55,734
Strider.

720
01:01:08,747 --> 01:01:11,959
VOICE OF THE RING:
<i>Baggins.</i>

721
01:01:14,795 --> 01:01:16,964
<i>Baggins.</i>

722
01:01:22,344 --> 01:01:27,474
<i>Baggins. Baggins.</i>

723
01:01:29,310 --> 01:01:31,604
PIPPIN:
Baggins? Sure, I know a Baggins.

724
01:01:32,396 --> 01:01:35,274
He's over there. Frodo Baggins.

725
01:01:35,441 --> 01:01:38,485
He's my second cousin,
once removed on his mother's side...

726
01:01:38,652 --> 01:01:40,946
...and my third cousin, twice removed...

727
01:01:45,451 --> 01:01:47,203
- Pippin!
- Steady on, Frodo.

728
01:02:16,732 --> 01:02:19,193
SAURON:
You cannot hide.

729
01:02:22,154 --> 01:02:25,324
I see you.

730
01:02:26,992 --> 01:02:29,703
There is no life...

731
01:02:29,870 --> 01:02:32,081
...in the void.

732
01:02:32,248 --> 01:02:33,749
Only...

733
01:02:34,667 --> 01:02:36,168
...death.

734
01:02:42,174 --> 01:02:47,054
You draw far too much attention
to yourself, "Mr. Underhill."

735
01:02:51,725 --> 01:02:52,768
What do you want?

736
01:02:52,977 --> 01:02:55,020
A little more caution from you.
That is no trinket you carry.

737
01:02:55,396 --> 01:02:58,399
-I carry nothing.
4ndeed.

738
01:02:58,691 --> 01:03:01,235
I can avoid being seen if I wish...

739
01:03:01,402 --> 01:03:05,114
...but to disappear entirely,
that is a rare gift.

740
01:03:05,614 --> 01:03:08,242
- Who are you?
- Are you frightened?

741
01:03:09,493 --> 01:03:10,536
Yes.

742
01:03:10,703 --> 01:03:14,623
Not nearly frightened enough.
I know what hunts you.

743
01:03:16,417 --> 01:03:17,876
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

744
01:03:18,627 --> 01:03:21,171
Let him go!
Or I'll have you, Longshanks.

745
01:03:22,840 --> 01:03:26,969
You have a stout heart, little Hobbit.
But that will not save you.

746
01:03:27,136 --> 01:03:30,055
You can no longer wait
for the wizard, Frodo.

747
01:03:30,222 --> 01:03:31,223
They're coming.

748
01:03:31,557 --> 01:03:34,393
[HORSE GRUNTS]

749
01:04:41,377 --> 01:04:43,629
[SCREECHING]

750
01:04:54,932 --> 01:04:56,433
What are they?

751
01:04:58,602 --> 01:05:00,729
They were once Men.

752
01:05:01,230 --> 01:05:03,440
Great kings of Men.

753
01:05:03,649 --> 01:05:06,819
Then Sauron the Deceiver gave to them
nine rings of power.

754
01:05:07,403 --> 01:05:10,489
Blinded by their greed,
they took them without question.

755
01:05:10,739 --> 01:05:14,076
One by one, falling into darkness.

756
01:05:14,243 --> 01:05:16,745
Now they are slaves to his will.

757
01:05:19,123 --> 01:05:20,833
They are the Nazgul.

758
01:05:20,999 --> 01:05:23,752
Ringwraiths. Neither living nor dead.

759
01:05:24,503 --> 01:05:25,963
At all times they feel...

760
01:05:26,130 --> 01:05:28,090
<i>...the presence of the Ring...</i>

761
01:05:28,257 --> 01:05:32,803
<i>...drawn to the power of the One.
They will never stop hunting you.</i>

762
01:05:42,771 --> 01:05:45,691
FRODO: Where are you taking us?
- Into the Wild.

763
01:05:53,866 --> 01:05:57,995
How do we know this Strider
is a friend of Gandalf?

764
01:05:58,162 --> 01:06:00,998
I think a servant of the enemy
would look fairer...

765
01:06:01,373 --> 01:06:05,294
- ...and feel fouler.
- He's foul enough.

766
01:06:05,878 --> 01:06:08,714
We have no choice but to trust him.

767
01:06:08,881 --> 01:06:12,342
-But where is he leading us?
STRIDER: To Rivendell, Master Gamgee.

768
01:06:14,720 --> 01:06:18,015
-To the house of Elrond.
SAM: Did you hear that? Rivendell.

769
01:06:18,557 --> 01:06:21,351
We're going to see the Elves.

770
01:06:38,619 --> 01:06:40,245
[HOBBITS WHISPERING]

771
01:06:42,998 --> 01:06:47,252
- Gentlemen, we do not stop till nightfall.
- What about breakfast?

772
01:06:47,419 --> 01:06:50,088
- You've already had it.
- We've had one, yes.

773
01:06:50,255 --> 01:06:52,508
What about second breakfast?

774
01:06:55,928 --> 01:06:59,097
Don't think he knows
about second breakfast, Pip.

775
01:06:59,264 --> 01:07:04,520
What about elevenses? Luncheon?
Afternoon tea? Dinner? Supper?

776
01:07:04,728 --> 01:07:08,899
- He knows about them, doesn't he?
- I wouldn't count on it.

777
01:07:14,363 --> 01:07:15,948
MERRY:
Pippin!

778
01:07:32,464 --> 01:07:35,968
What do they eat
when they can't get Hobbit?

779
01:07:56,405 --> 01:07:59,324
[STRIDER HUMS]

780
01:08:03,787 --> 01:08:07,416
[STRIDER SINGS IN ELVISH]

781
01:08:14,631 --> 01:08:16,842
Who is she?

782
01:08:17,509 --> 01:08:20,137
This woman you sing of.

783
01:08:23,515 --> 01:08:25,976
'Tis the lady of Luthien.

784
01:08:26,143 --> 01:08:31,315
The Elf-maiden who gave her love
to Beren, a mortal.

785
01:08:33,150 --> 01:08:35,277
What happened to her?

786
01:08:37,487 --> 01:08:39,990
She died.

787
01:08:44,036 --> 01:08:46,371
Get some sleep, Frodo.

788
01:08:56,632 --> 01:09:00,719
SARU MAN: <i>The power of Isengard
is at your command...</i>

789
01:09:00,886 --> 01:09:05,349
<i>...Sauron, Lord of the Earth.</i>

790
01:09:06,016 --> 01:09:08,352
[VOICES WHISPERING IN BLACK SPEECH]

791
01:09:08,685 --> 01:09:14,483
<i>SAURON:
Build me an army worthy of Mordor.</i>

792
01:09:20,197 --> 01:09:24,660
What orders from Mordor, my lord?
What does the Eye command?

793
01:09:25,077 --> 01:09:27,037
We have work to do.

794
01:10:09,621 --> 01:10:14,251
The trees are strong, my lord.
Their roots go deep.

795
01:10:14,626 --> 01:10:16,461
Rip them all down.

796
01:10:43,905 --> 01:10:46,783
This was the great watchtower
of Amon SCH.

797
01:10:48,493 --> 01:10:51,163
We shall rest here tonight.

798
01:11:02,883 --> 01:11:06,303
These are for you.
Keep them close.

799
01:11:06,511 --> 01:11:09,014
I'm going to have a look around.

800
01:11:11,391 --> 01:11:13,310
Stay here.

801
01:11:15,854 --> 01:11:18,023
MERRY:
My tomato's burst.

802
01:11:18,273 --> 01:11:20,150
PIPPIN:
Could I have some bacon?

803
01:11:20,358 --> 01:11:22,319
MERRY:
Want a tomato, Sam?

804
01:11:22,694 --> 01:11:26,364
- What are you doing?!
- Tomatoes, sausages, nice crispy bacon.

805
01:11:26,531 --> 01:11:29,284
SAM: We saved some for you, Mr. Frodo.
FRODO: Put it out, you fools!

806
01:11:29,493 --> 01:11:33,497
—Put it out!
PIPPIN: That's nice! Ash on my tomatoes!

807
01:11:34,039 --> 01:11:36,166
[RI NGWRAITHS SCREECH I NG]

808
01:11:41,922 --> 01:11:43,673
Go!

809
01:12:37,102 --> 01:12:38,562
Back, you devils!

810
01:12:49,030 --> 01:12:51,616
[VOICE OF THE RING
SPEAKS IN BLACK SPEECH]

811
01:13:30,822 --> 01:13:33,783
[VOICE OF THE RING
SPEAKS IN BLACK SPEECH]

812
01:14:02,062 --> 01:14:03,313
Frodo!

813
01:14:07,359 --> 01:14:09,194
- Frodo.
- Oh, Sam.

814
01:14:46,231 --> 01:14:47,232
Strider!

815
01:14:50,026 --> 01:14:55,532
- Help him, Strider.
- He's been stabbed by a Morgul blade.

816
01:14:57,033 --> 01:15:01,913
This is beyond my skill to heal.
He needs Elvish medicine.

817
01:15:06,501 --> 01:15:07,544
Hurry!

818
01:15:07,752 --> 01:15:11,715
We're six days from Rivendell!
He'll never make it!

819
01:15:11,923 --> 01:15:13,758
Hold on, Frodo.

820
01:15:14,134 --> 01:15:15,343
Gandalf!

821
01:15:33,278 --> 01:15:36,406
[METAL CLANKING]

822
01:16:14,110 --> 01:16:17,322
[WHISPERS INSTRUCTIONS TO THE MOTH]

823
01:17:09,749 --> 01:17:11,042
[GROWLS]

824
01:17:54,294 --> 01:17:57,380
Look, Frodo. It's Mr. Bilbo's trolls.

825
01:17:59,549 --> 01:18:02,385
Mr. Frodo? He's going cold.

826
01:18:05,346 --> 01:18:07,098
Is he going to die?

827
01:18:07,307 --> 01:18:12,187
He's passing into the Shadow World.
He'll soon become a Wraith like them.

828
01:18:12,437 --> 01:18:14,022
[RI NGWRAITHS SCREECH I NG]

829
01:18:17,358 --> 01:18:21,196
- They're close.
- Sam, do you know the Athelas plant?

830
01:18:21,362 --> 01:18:22,864
- Athe|as?
- Kingsfoi|.

831
01:18:23,031 --> 01:18:24,115
Kingsfoil, aye, it's a weed.

832
01:18:24,324 --> 01:18:27,452
It may help to slow the poisoning.
Hurry!

833
01:18:41,841 --> 01:18:45,970
FEMALE: What's this?
A Ranger caught off his guard?

834
01:19:10,870 --> 01:19:11,913
Frodo.

835
01:19:13,873 --> 01:19:17,001
[IN ELVISH]
I am Arwen - I've come to help you.

836
01:19:19,420 --> 01:19:21,256
Hear my voice...

837
01:19:21,506 --> 01:19:23,633
Come back to the light.

838
01:19:28,846 --> 01:19:30,682
Who is she?

839
01:19:31,349 --> 01:19:33,101
[IN ENGLISH]
Frodo.

840
01:19:33,351 --> 01:19:36,854
- She's an Elf.
- He's fading.

841
01:19:39,107 --> 01:19:41,276
He's not going to last.

842
01:19:41,484 --> 01:19:44,153
We must get him to my father.

843
01:19:44,904 --> 01:19:47,782
- I've been looking for you for two days.
- Where are you taking him?

844
01:19:47,949 --> 01:19:54,038
There are five Wraiths behind you.
Where the other four are, I do not know.

845
01:19:55,123 --> 01:19:57,542
[IN ELVISH] Stay with the Hobbits -
I'll send horses for you.

846
01:19:57,709 --> 01:19:59,460
[IN ELVISH]
I'm the faster rider - I'll take him.

847
01:20:00,295 --> 01:20:01,671
The Road is too dangerous.

848
01:20:01,879 --> 01:20:03,131
What are they saying?

849
01:20:03,339 --> 01:20:05,383
ARWEN:
[fl can get across the river...

850
01:20:05,591 --> 01:20:08,177
...the power of my people
will protect him.

851
01:20:09,220 --> 01:20:10,888
[IN ENGLISH]
I do not fear them.

852
01:20:14,684 --> 01:20:16,644
[SPEAKS ELVISH]

853
01:20:20,732 --> 01:20:22,150
[IN ENGLISH]
Arwen...

854
01:20:22,317 --> 01:20:25,528
...ride hard. Don't look back.

855
01:20:30,575 --> 01:20:34,954
What are you doing?!
Those Wraiths are still out there!

856
01:21:41,813 --> 01:21:42,980
[SCREECHES]

857
01:21:45,108 --> 01:21:47,652
[SPEAKS ELVISH]

858
01:22:29,569 --> 01:22:32,280
Give up the half ling, She-Elf.

859
01:22:33,197 --> 01:22:35,783
If you want him, come and claim him.

860
01:22:47,837 --> 01:22:50,047
[SPEAKS ELVISH]

861
01:23:29,670 --> 01:23:32,173
No. No!

862
01:23:35,426 --> 01:23:37,720
Frodo, no.

863
01:23:37,929 --> 01:23:40,223
Frodo, don't give in.

864
01:23:40,431 --> 01:23:42,433
Not now.

865
01:23:53,361 --> 01:23:55,863
<i>ARWEN:
What grace is given me...</i>

866
01:23:56,531 --> 01:23:58,366
<i>...let it pass to him.</i>

867
01:23:58,616 --> 01:24:00,743
<i>Let him be spared.</i>

868
01:24:01,369 --> 01:24:03,412
<i>Save him.</i>

869
01:24:05,373 --> 01:24:08,793
[SPEAKS ELVISH]

870
01:24:15,800 --> 01:24:20,972
-Where am I?
GANDALF: You are in the house of Elrond.

871
01:24:21,430 --> 01:24:27,937
And it is 10:00 in the morning
on October 24th, if you want to know.

872
01:24:29,897 --> 01:24:33,693
- Gandalf!
- Yes, I'm here.

873
01:24:35,319 --> 01:24:38,406
And you're lucky to be here too.

874
01:24:39,073 --> 01:24:43,077
A few more hours and you
would have been beyond our aid.

875
01:24:43,286 --> 01:24:47,415
But you have some strength in you,
my dear Hobbit.

876
01:24:55,006 --> 01:24:57,508
What happened, Gandalf?

877
01:24:58,467 --> 01:25:03,848
- Why didn't you meet us?
- I am sorry, Frodo.

878
01:25:08,603 --> 01:25:10,354
I was delayed.

879
01:25:11,230 --> 01:25:15,443
A friendship with Saruman
is not lightly thrown aside.

880
01:25:19,530 --> 01:25:24,201
One ill turn deserves another.
It is over.

881
01:25:24,493 --> 01:25:27,246
Embrace the power of the Ring...

882
01:25:27,788 --> 01:25:30,333
...or embrace your own destruction!

883
01:25:32,627 --> 01:25:36,505
GANDALF:
There is only one Lord of the Ring.

884
01:25:36,756 --> 01:25:40,760
Only one who can bend it to his will.

885
01:25:41,552 --> 01:25:45,514
And he does not share power.

886
01:25:45,765 --> 01:25:48,517
[BIRD SCREECHES]

887
01:25:59,862 --> 01:26:03,240
So you have chosen death.

888
01:26:13,292 --> 01:26:17,088
Gandalf? What is it?

889
01:26:18,047 --> 01:26:19,840
Nothing, Frodo.

890
01:26:20,508 --> 01:26:22,343
SAM:
Frodo!

891
01:26:22,551 --> 01:26:23,594
Frodo!

892
01:26:23,803 --> 01:26:26,180
- Sam.
- Bless you, you're awake!

893
01:26:26,389 --> 01:26:29,100
Sam has hardly left your side.

894
01:26:29,350 --> 01:26:31,519
We were that worried about you.
Weren't we, Mr. Gandalf?

895
01:26:31,894 --> 01:26:37,024
By the skills of Lord Elrond,
you're beginning to mend.

896
01:26:38,526 --> 01:26:42,113
Welcome to Rivendell, Frodo Baggins.

897
01:27:30,161 --> 01:27:33,497
FRODO: Bilbo!
- Hello, Frodo, my lad.

898
01:27:33,664 --> 01:27:35,374
Bilbo.

899
01:27:40,379 --> 01:27:42,131
<i>FRODO:
"There and Back Again:</i>

900
01:27:42,381 --> 01:27:45,134
<i>A Hobbit's Tale,</i> by Bilbo Baggins."

901
01:27:48,179 --> 01:27:51,766
- This is wonderful.
- I meant to go back...

902
01:27:52,099 --> 01:27:55,895
...wonder at the powers of Mirkwood...

903
01:27:56,353 --> 01:27:58,647
...visit Lake-town...

904
01:27:58,898 --> 01:28:02,276
...see the Lonely Mountain again.

905
01:28:02,693 --> 01:28:07,615
But age, it seems,
has finally caught up with me.

906
01:28:19,710 --> 01:28:21,504
FRODO:
I miss the Shire.

907
01:28:21,921 --> 01:28:27,051
I spent all my childhood pretending
I was off somewhere else.

908
01:28:27,384 --> 01:28:30,971
Off with you,
on one of your adventures.

909
01:28:33,933 --> 01:28:37,520
But my own adventure turned out
to be quite different.

910
01:28:42,733 --> 01:28:45,945
I'm not like you, Bilbo.

911
01:28:47,071 --> 01:28:49,406
My dear boy.

912
01:28:53,494 --> 01:28:57,456
SAM: Now, what have I forgotten?
- Packed already?

913
01:28:58,249 --> 01:29:00,042
No harm in being prepared.

914
01:29:00,251 --> 01:29:02,837
- I thought you wanted to see the Elves.
- I do.

915
01:29:03,003 --> 01:29:05,923
- More than anything.
- I did.

916
01:29:06,090 --> 01:29:08,008
It's just...

917
01:29:08,759 --> 01:29:11,428
We did what Gandalf wanted, didn't we?

918
01:29:11,595 --> 01:29:15,266
We got the Ring this far,
to Rivendell. And I thought...

919
01:29:15,474 --> 01:29:18,769
...seeing as how you're on the mend,
we'd be off soon.

920
01:29:18,978 --> 01:29:20,688
Off home.

921
01:29:24,859 --> 01:29:26,861
You are right, <i>Sam.</i>

922
01:29:29,029 --> 01:29:31,782
We did what we set out to do.

923
01:29:32,366 --> 01:29:34,952
The Ring will be safe in Rivendell.

924
01:29:39,039 --> 01:29:41,375
I am ready to go home.

925
01:29:42,126 --> 01:29:44,211
ELROND:
His strength returns.

926
01:29:44,378 --> 01:29:50,092
That wound will never fully heal.
He will carry it the rest of his life.

927
01:29:50,634 --> 01:29:53,220
And yet to have come so far
still bearing the Ring...

928
01:29:53,387 --> 01:29:57,099
...the Hobbit has shown extraordinary
resilience to its evil.

929
01:29:57,308 --> 01:30:00,644
It is a burden he should never
have had to bear.

930
01:30:00,895 --> 01:30:06,317
- We can ask no more of Frodo.
- Gandalf, the enemy is moving.

931
01:30:06,525 --> 01:30:11,155
Sauron's forces are massing in the East.
His Eye is fixed on Rivendell.

932
01:30:11,405 --> 01:30:14,158
And Saruman, you tell me, has betrayed us.

933
01:30:14,325 --> 01:30:17,578
Our list of allies grows thin.

934
01:30:18,329 --> 01:30:21,123
His treachery runs deeper
than you know.

935
01:30:21,332 --> 01:30:25,002
By foul craft, Saruman
has crossed Orcs with Goblin-men.

936
01:30:25,169 --> 01:30:27,630
He's breeding an army
in the caverns of Isengard.

937
01:30:27,922 --> 01:30:32,509
An army that can move in sunlight
and cover great distance at speed.

938
01:30:32,676 --> 01:30:35,095
Saruman is coming for the Ring.

939
01:30:35,554 --> 01:30:39,600
This evil cannot be concealed
by the power of the Elves.

940
01:30:39,808 --> 01:30:44,188
We do not have the strength
to fight both Mordor and Isengard!

941
01:30:48,025 --> 01:30:49,109
Gandalf...

942
01:30:50,444 --> 01:30:53,030
...the Ring cannot stay here.

943
01:31:12,549 --> 01:31:15,719
ELROND: <i>This peril belongs
to all Middle-earth.</i>

944
01:31:15,970 --> 01:31:18,681
<i>They must decide now how to end it.</i>

945
01:31:19,723 --> 01:31:23,310
The time of the Elves is over.
My people are leaving these shores.

946
01:31:23,978 --> 01:31:27,564
Who will you look to when we've gone?
The Dwarves?

947
01:31:27,731 --> 01:31:32,861
They hide in mountains seeking riches.
They care not for the troubles of others.

948
01:31:34,488 --> 01:31:37,324
It is in Men
that we must place our hope.

949
01:31:37,658 --> 01:31:39,368
Men?

950
01:31:40,244 --> 01:31:43,497
Men are weak.
The race of Men is failing.

951
01:31:43,664 --> 01:31:48,127
The blood of Numenor is all but spent,
its pride and dignity forgotten.

952
01:31:48,419 --> 01:31:51,922
It is because of Men
the Ring survives.

953
01:31:52,131 --> 01:31:53,757
I was there, Gandalf.

954
01:31:54,425 --> 01:31:57,261
<i>I was there 3000 years ago...</i>

955
01:32:04,101 --> 01:32:06,520
<i>...when lsildur took the Ring.</i>

956
01:32:06,687 --> 01:32:10,607
I was there the day
the strength of Men failed.

957
01:32:13,152 --> 01:32:15,696
Isildur, hurry! Follow me.

958
01:32:17,281 --> 01:32:20,909
ELROND: <i>I led lsildur into the heart
of Mount Doom...</i>

959
01:32:21,160 --> 01:32:24,705
<i>...where the Ring was forged,
the one place it could be destroyed.</i>

960
01:32:24,872 --> 01:32:27,458
Cast it into the fire!

961
01:32:27,791 --> 01:32:30,627
[VOICE OF THE RING
WHISPERS IN BLACK SPEECH]

962
01:32:32,629 --> 01:32:36,425
- Destroy it!
- No.

963
01:32:37,760 --> 01:32:39,928
Isildur!

964
01:32:40,387 --> 01:32:45,142
ELROND: <i>It should have ended that day,
but evil was allowed to endure.</i>

965
01:32:49,229 --> 01:32:53,484
Isildur kept the Ring.
The line of kings is broken.

966
01:32:54,401 --> 01:32:58,072
There's no strength left
in the world of Men.

967
01:32:58,238 --> 01:33:03,077
- They're scattered, divided, leaderless.
- There is one who could unite them.

968
01:33:03,285 --> 01:33:06,663
One who could reclaim
the throne of Gondor.

969
01:33:08,332 --> 01:33:12,169
He turned from that path
a long time ago.

970
01:33:12,336 --> 01:33:14,463
He has chosen exile.

971
01:33:45,702 --> 01:33:47,704
You are no Elf.

972
01:33:47,871 --> 01:33:49,957
Men of the South are welcome here.

973
01:33:50,541 --> 01:33:54,044
- Who are you?
- I am a friend to Gandalf the Grey.

974
01:33:55,546 --> 01:33:58,382
Then we are here on common purpose...

975
01:33:58,757 --> 01:34:00,217
<i>...Mend.</i>

976
01:34:15,399 --> 01:34:18,318
The shards of Narsil.

977
01:34:21,780 --> 01:34:26,243
The blade that cut the Ring
from Sauron's hand.

978
01:34:29,163 --> 01:34:31,415
It's still sharp.

979
01:34:40,299 --> 01:34:43,385
But no more than a broken heirloom.

980
01:35:10,204 --> 01:35:13,248
Why do you fear the past?

981
01:35:14,124 --> 01:35:19,463
You are lsildur's heir,
not lsildur himself.

982
01:35:19,713 --> 01:35:23,133
You are not bound to his fate.

983
01:35:23,634 --> 01:35:27,638
The same blood flows in my veins.

984
01:35:30,641 --> 01:35:33,227
The same weakness.

985
01:35:35,938 --> 01:35:38,732
Your time will come.

986
01:35:38,941 --> 01:35:43,320
You will face the same evil.
And you will defeat it.

987
01:35:46,490 --> 01:35:48,867
[IN ELVISH]
The Shadow does not hold sway yet.

988
01:35:49,868 --> 01:35:53,497
<i>“Fit over YO“... not over me.</i>

989
01:36:04,841 --> 01:36:08,053
Do you remember when we first met?

990
01:36:11,598 --> 01:36:16,186
[IN ELVISH]
I thought I had strayed into a dream.

991
01:36:16,687 --> 01:36:19,189
Long years have passed.

992
01:36:20,899 --> 01:36:24,278
You did not have the cares you carry now.

993
01:36:25,737 --> 01:36:27,781
Do you remember what I told you?

994
01:36:33,870 --> 01:36:36,540
[IN ENGLISH]
You said you'd bind yourself to me...

995
01:36:38,542 --> 01:36:43,547
...forsaking the immortal life
of your people.

996
01:36:44,673 --> 01:36:46,550
[IN ENGLISH]
And to that I hold.

997
01:36:46,717 --> 01:36:50,345
I would rather share
one lifetime with you...

998
01:36:50,595 --> 01:36:54,474
...than face all the Ages
of this world alone.

999
01:37:03,233 --> 01:37:06,695
I choose a mortal life.

1000
01:37:08,030 --> 01:37:12,284
- You cannot give me this.
- It is mine to give to whom I will...

1001
01:37:15,537 --> 01:37:18,040
...like my heart.

1002
01:37:33,805 --> 01:37:37,517
ELROND: Strangers from distant lands,
friends of old...

1003
01:37:37,726 --> 01:37:41,646
...you've been summoned here
to answer the threat of Mordor.

1004
01:37:42,272 --> 01:37:47,152
Middle-earth stands upon the brink
of destruction. None can escape it.

1005
01:37:47,402 --> 01:37:50,906
You will unite, or you will fall.

1006
01:37:51,114 --> 01:37:55,410
Each race is bound to this fate,
this one doom.

1007
01:37:57,245 --> 01:38:00,749
Bring forth the Ring, Frodo.

1008
01:38:14,805 --> 01:38:16,556
So it is true.

1009
01:38:33,990 --> 01:38:36,118
In a dream...

1010
01:38:37,702 --> 01:38:40,831
...I saw the eastern sky grow dark...

1011
01:38:41,123 --> 01:38:42,833
...but in the West
a pale light lingered.

1012
01:38:43,625 --> 01:38:45,377
A voice was crying:

1013
01:38:45,669 --> 01:38:48,588
"Your doom is near at hand.

1014
01:38:49,589 --> 01:38:52,342
Isildur's Bane is found."

1015
01:38:56,346 --> 01:38:58,181
Isildur's Bane.

1016
01:38:58,849 --> 01:39:00,142
Boromir!

1017
01:39:00,350 --> 01:39:03,979
[GANDALF CHANTS IN BLACK SPEECH]

1018
01:39:04,479 --> 01:39:08,024
[VOICE OF THE RING
ECHOES IN BLACK SPEECH]

1019
01:39:23,331 --> 01:39:27,169
Never before has any voice uttered the
words of that tongue here in Imladris.

1020
01:39:27,335 --> 01:39:31,047
I do not ask your pardon,
Master Elrond...

1021
01:39:31,214 --> 01:39:33,341
...for the Black Speech of Mordor...

1022
01:39:33,633 --> 01:39:35,010
...may yet be heard...

1023
01:39:35,177 --> 01:39:38,180
...in every corner of the West!

1024
01:39:38,346 --> 01:39:41,016
The Ring is altogether evil.

1025
01:39:41,349 --> 01:39:42,851
It is a gift.

1026
01:39:43,435 --> 01:39:45,520
A gift to the foes of Mordor.

1027
01:39:46,146 --> 01:39:48,231
Why not use this Ring?

1028
01:39:48,440 --> 01:39:51,193
<i>Long has my father,
the Steward of Gender...</i>

1029
01:39:51,401 --> 01:39:55,739
...kept the forces of Mordor at bay.
By the blood of our people...

1030
01:39:56,031 --> 01:39:58,241
...are your lands kept safe.

1031
01:40:00,035 --> 01:40:04,372
Give Gondor the weapon of the enemy.
Let us use it against him.

1032
01:40:04,664 --> 01:40:08,418
You cannot wield it.
None of us can.

1033
01:40:09,044 --> 01:40:13,089
The One Ring answers to Sauron alone.
It has no other master.

1034
01:40:13,256 --> 01:40:16,801
And what would a Ranger know
of this matter?

1035
01:40:17,093 --> 01:40:19,095
This is no mere Ranger.

1036
01:40:20,096 --> 01:40:23,767
He is Aragorn, son of Arathorn.

1037
01:40:24,267 --> 01:40:27,187
You owe him your allegiance.

1038
01:40:31,274 --> 01:40:33,193
Aragorn.

1039
01:40:34,945 --> 01:40:37,781
This is Isildur's heir?

1040
01:40:40,116 --> 01:40:42,827
And heir to the throne of Gondor.

1041
01:40:44,955 --> 01:40:46,414
[IN ELVISH]
Sit down, Legolas.

1042
01:40:49,793 --> 01:40:52,629
Gondor has no king.

1043
01:40:54,464 --> 01:40:56,132
Gondor needs no king.

1044
01:41:02,806 --> 01:41:06,476
Aragorn is right. We cannot use it.

1045
01:41:07,477 --> 01:41:10,981
You have only one choice.

1046
01:41:11,231 --> 01:41:13,608
The Ring must be destroyed.

1047
01:41:15,443 --> 01:41:18,530
[VOICE OF THE RING
WHISPERS IN BLACK SPEECH]

1048
01:41:18,822 --> 01:41:21,366
What are we waiting for?

1049
01:41:27,289 --> 01:41:31,501
[VOICE OF THE RING
SPEAKS IN BLACK SPEECH]

1050
01:41:33,503 --> 01:41:36,506
The Ring cannot be destroyed, Gimli,
son of Gléin...

1051
01:41:36,756 --> 01:41:41,011
...by any craft that we here possess.

1052
01:41:41,511 --> 01:41:45,682
The Ring was made in the fires
of Mount Doom.

1053
01:41:45,849 --> 01:41:49,686
Only there can it be unmade.

1054
01:41:50,729 --> 01:41:53,356
It must be taken deep into Mordor...

1055
01:41:53,523 --> 01:41:58,528
...and cast back into the fiery chasm
from whence it came.

1056
01:41:58,695 --> 01:41:59,779
[VOICE OF THE RING
WHISPERS IN BLACK SPEECH]

1057
01:42:00,530 --> 01:42:02,532
One of you...

1058
01:42:03,033 --> 01:42:05,201
...must do this.

1059
01:42:08,121 --> 01:42:11,833
One does not simply walk into Mordor.

1060
01:42:12,709 --> 01:42:16,379
Its Black Gates are guarded
by more than just Orcs.

1061
01:42:17,213 --> 01:42:21,343
There is evil there
that does not sleep.

1062
01:42:21,551 --> 01:42:25,764
The Great Eye is ever-watchful.

1063
01:42:26,556 --> 01:42:28,558
It is a barren wasteland...

1064
01:42:28,767 --> 01:42:32,395
...riddled with fire, and ash
and dust.

1065
01:42:32,562 --> 01:42:36,399
The very air you breathe
is a poisonous fume.

1066
01:42:36,650 --> 01:42:40,904
Not with 10,000 men
could you do this. It is folly.

1067
01:42:41,154 --> 01:42:45,575
Have you heard nothing Lord Elrond
has said? The Ring must be destroyed.

1068
01:42:45,784 --> 01:42:48,411
And I suppose you think
you are the one to do it!

1069
01:42:48,578 --> 01:42:53,249
And if we fail, what then? What happens
when Sauron takes back what is his?

1070
01:42:53,416 --> 01:42:58,755
I will be dead before I see the Ring
in the hands of an Elf!

1071
01:42:58,922 --> 01:43:00,548
[SHOUTING]

1072
01:43:00,757 --> 01:43:03,259
Never trust an Elf!

1073
01:43:04,427 --> 01:43:10,266
GANDALF: Do you not understand?
While you bicker, Sauron's power grows!

1074
01:43:10,600 --> 01:43:13,436
None can escape it!
You'll all be destroyed!

1075
01:43:14,771 --> 01:43:18,441
[VOICE OF THE RING
WHISPERS IN BLACK SPEECH]

1076
01:43:32,247 --> 01:43:34,457
I Will take it.

1077
01:43:36,459 --> 01:43:38,962
I Will take it.

1078
01:43:44,801 --> 01:43:47,846
I will take the Ring to Mordor.

1079
01:43:55,895 --> 01:43:57,147
Though...

1080
01:44:00,233 --> 01:44:02,068
...I do not know the way.

1081
01:44:04,070 --> 01:44:08,408
I will help you bear
this burden, Frodo Baggins...

1082
01:44:08,575 --> 01:44:11,953
...as long as it is yours to bear.

1083
01:44:13,079 --> 01:44:16,166
If by my life
or death I can protect you...

1084
01:44:16,916 --> 01:44:18,251
...I Will.

1085
01:44:21,463 --> 01:44:23,757
You have my sword.

1086
01:44:25,592 --> 01:44:27,677
And you have my bow.

1087
01:44:28,261 --> 01:44:30,764
And my ax.

1088
01:44:37,771 --> 01:44:40,774
You carry the fates
of us all, little one.

1089
01:44:42,776 --> 01:44:46,446
If this is indeed
the will of the Council...

1090
01:44:46,905 --> 01:44:49,324
- ...then Gondor will see it done.
- Hey!

1091
01:44:51,951 --> 01:44:56,706
- Frodo's not going anywhere without me.
- It is hardly possible to separate you...

1092
01:44:56,915 --> 01:45:01,795
...even when he is summoned
to a secret Council and you are not.

1093
01:45:02,295 --> 01:45:04,255
We're coming too!

1094
01:45:06,382 --> 01:45:09,135
You'll have to send us home
tied up in a sack to stop us.

1095
01:45:09,385 --> 01:45:12,722
Anyway, you need people
of intelligence on this sort of...

1096
01:45:13,056 --> 01:45:14,390
...mission.

1097
01:45:14,557 --> 01:45:16,059
Quest.

1098
01:45:16,518 --> 01:45:17,560
Thing.

1099
01:45:19,395 --> 01:45:22,065
Well, that rules you out, Pip.

1100
01:45:23,650 --> 01:45:25,568
Nine companions.

1101
01:45:27,403 --> 01:45:29,239
So be it.

1102
01:45:29,572 --> 01:45:32,575
You shall be
the Fellowship of the Ring.

1103
01:45:33,243 --> 01:45:35,078
Great!

1104
01:45:35,286 --> 01:45:37,580
Where are we going?

1105
01:46:13,142 --> 01:46:15,686
ELROND [IN ELVISH]:
She wanted to protect her child...

1106
01:46:17,521 --> 01:46:21,317
she thought in Rivendell
you would be safe.

1107
01:46:23,653 --> 01:46:27,156
[IN ENGLISH] In her heart, your mother
knew you'd be hunted all your life.

1108
01:46:27,657 --> 01:46:29,325
That you'd never escape your fate.

1109
01:46:29,825 --> 01:46:33,496
The skill of the Elves
can reforge the sword of kings...

1110
01:46:33,913 --> 01:46:37,833
...but only you have the power
to wield it.

1111
01:46:38,834 --> 01:46:41,337
I do not want that power.

1112
01:46:41,504 --> 01:46:44,173
I have never wanted it.

1113
01:46:45,508 --> 01:46:48,135
You are the last of that bloodline.
There is no other.

1114
01:46:52,515 --> 01:46:54,850
BILBO:
My old sword! Sting.

1115
01:46:55,059 --> 01:46:56,185
Here, take it. Take it.

1116
01:47:01,691 --> 01:47:05,653
- It's so light.
- Yes. Made by the Elves, you know.

1117
01:47:06,362 --> 01:47:10,449
The blade glows blue
when Orcs are close.

1118
01:47:10,658 --> 01:47:15,204
And it's times like that, my lad,
when you have to be extra careful.

1119
01:47:15,413 --> 01:47:17,873
Here's a pretty thing.

1120
01:47:18,290 --> 01:47:19,583
Mithril.

1121
01:47:20,376 --> 01:47:24,755
As light as a feather,
and as hard as dragon scales.

1122
01:47:24,964 --> 01:47:28,217
Let me see you put it on. Come on.

1123
01:47:31,762 --> 01:47:33,222
Oh!

1124
01:47:36,267 --> 01:47:38,310
My old ring.

1125
01:47:39,562 --> 01:47:43,482
I should very much like...

1126
01:47:43,733 --> 01:47:47,737
...to hold it again, one last time.

1127
01:48:05,087 --> 01:48:08,758
I'm sorry I brought this upon you,
my boy.

1128
01:48:09,091 --> 01:48:13,220
I'm sorry that you
must carry this burden.

1129
01:48:17,725 --> 01:48:20,770
I'm sorry for everything.

1130
01:48:35,826 --> 01:48:39,997
The Ring-bearer is setting out
on the Quest of Mount Doom.

1131
01:48:41,332 --> 01:48:43,959
On you who travel with him,
no oath...

1132
01:48:44,168 --> 01:48:47,296
...nor bond is laid to go further
than you will.

1133
01:48:50,758 --> 01:48:53,302
Farewell. Hold to your purpose.

1134
01:48:53,761 --> 01:48:57,681
May the blessings of Elves and Men...

1135
01:48:58,224 --> 01:49:00,810
...and all Free Folk go with you.

1136
01:49:03,896 --> 01:49:07,983
The Fellowship awaits the Ring-bearer.

1137
01:49:26,418 --> 01:49:28,921
Mordor, Gandalf, is it left or right?

1138
01:49:29,463 --> 01:49:31,298
Left.

1139
01:50:50,794 --> 01:50:55,216
<i>GANDALF: We must hold to this course,
west of the Misty Mountains, for 40 days.</i>

1140
01:50:55,424 --> 01:50:59,178
<i>If our luck holds, the Gap of Rohan
will still be open to us.</i>

1141
01:50:59,386 --> 01:51:02,932
<i>From there, our road
turns east to Mordor.</i>

1142
01:51:03,098 --> 01:51:06,936
Two, one, five. Good! Very good.

1143
01:51:08,771 --> 01:51:09,813
Move your feet.

1144
01:51:10,022 --> 01:51:11,357
MERRY: You look good, Pippin.
- Thanks.

1145
01:51:11,565 --> 01:51:12,942
BOROMIR:
Faster!

1146
01:51:14,318 --> 01:51:18,113
If anyone was to ask for my opinion,
which I note they're not...

1147
01:51:18,322 --> 01:51:21,075
...I'd say we were taking
the long way 'round.

1148
01:51:21,575 --> 01:51:24,620
Gandalf, we could pass through
the Mines of Moria.

1149
01:51:25,287 --> 01:51:29,124
My cousin Balin would give us
a royal welcome.

1150
01:51:29,458 --> 01:51:34,838
No, I would not take the road through
Moria unless I had no other choice.

1151
01:51:44,056 --> 01:51:45,140
Sorry!

1152
01:51:45,975 --> 01:51:47,476
MERRY:
Get him!

1153
01:51:48,811 --> 01:51:51,272
MERRY: For the Shire!
PIPPIN: Hold him. Hold him down, Merry!

1154
01:51:51,814 --> 01:51:54,149
Gentlemen, that's enough.

1155
01:51:57,945 --> 01:51:59,571
MERRY: You've got my arm!
You've got my arm!

1156
01:51:59,989 --> 01:52:02,658
- What is that?
- Nothing. It's just a wisp of cloud.

1157
01:52:02,908 --> 01:52:05,619
It's moving fast.

1158
01:52:05,828 --> 01:52:07,997
Against the wind.

1159
01:52:08,789 --> 01:52:10,916
- Crebain from Dunland!
- Hide!

1160
01:52:11,125 --> 01:52:13,836
- Hurry!
- Take cover!

1161
01:52:47,244 --> 01:52:48,996
Spies of Saruman.

1162
01:52:49,747 --> 01:52:53,042
The passage south is being watched.

1163
01:52:54,209 --> 01:52:57,546
We must take the Pass of Caradhras.

1164
01:53:10,184 --> 01:53:11,894
ARAGORN:
Frodo!

1165
01:53:30,871 --> 01:53:33,123
Boromir.

1166
01:53:33,374 --> 01:53:37,586
It is a strange fate that we should
suffer so much fear and doubt...

1167
01:53:37,795 --> 01:53:40,923
...over so small a thing.

1168
01:53:44,134 --> 01:53:46,095
Such a little thing.

1169
01:53:46,303 --> 01:53:47,763
Boromir!

1170
01:53:48,389 --> 01:53:51,100
Give the Ring to Frodo.

1171
01:54:00,901 --> 01:54:02,945
As you wish.

1172
01:54:03,654 --> 01:54:05,656
I care not.

1173
01:54:10,119 --> 01:54:12,454
[BOROMIR CHUCKLES]

1174
01:54:22,840 --> 01:54:25,634
[BIRDS SQUAWKING]

1175
01:54:41,066 --> 01:54:45,779
So, Gandalf, you try
to lead them over Caradhras.

1176
01:54:45,988 --> 01:54:50,576
And if that fails,
where then will you go?

1177
01:54:51,869 --> 01:54:54,830
<i>If the mountain defeats you...</i>

1178
01:54:55,080 --> 01:54:59,501
<i>...will you risk
a more dangerous road?</i>

1179
01:55:06,008 --> 01:55:08,677
[SARUMAN CHANTS IN QUENYA]

1180
01:55:11,847 --> 01:55:14,725
There is a fell voice on the air.

1181
01:55:15,851 --> 01:55:17,352
It's Saruman!

1182
01:55:26,236 --> 01:55:30,908
He's trying to bring down the mountain!
Gandalf, we must turn back!

1183
01:55:31,200 --> 01:55:32,993
No!

1184
01:55:35,996 --> 01:55:38,832
[CHANTS IN SINDARIN]

1185
01:56:39,434 --> 01:56:41,270
We must get off the mountain!

1186
01:56:41,770 --> 01:56:46,108
Make for the Gap of Rohan,
and take the west road to my city!

1187
01:56:46,275 --> 01:56:49,611
The Gap of Rohan takes us
too close to Isengard!

1188
01:56:49,778 --> 01:56:53,532
GIMLI: We cannot pass over a mountain.
Let us go under it.

1189
01:56:53,782 --> 01:56:56,618
Let us go through the Mines of Moria.

1190
01:56:58,453 --> 01:57:02,291
SARUMAN: <i>Moria. You fear to go
into those mines.</i>

1191
01:57:02,958 --> 01:57:07,963
The Dwarves delved too greedily
and too deep.

1192
01:57:08,797 --> 01:57:13,677
<i>You know what they awoke
in the darkness of Khazad-dflm:</i>

1193
01:57:14,970 --> 01:57:18,473
Shadow and flame.

1194
01:57:21,810 --> 01:57:24,479
Let the Ring-bearer decide.

1195
01:57:29,192 --> 01:57:31,320
We cannot stay here!

1196
01:57:31,486 --> 01:57:34,323
This will be the death of the Hobbits.

1197
01:57:34,489 --> 01:57:36,199
Frodo?

1198
01:57:39,202 --> 01:57:42,080
We will go through the mines.

1199
01:57:42,831 --> 01:57:44,708
So be it.

1200
01:57:51,381 --> 01:57:55,344
Frodo, come and help an old man.

1201
01:57:58,847 --> 01:58:01,058
How is your shoulder?

1202
01:58:01,266 --> 01:58:04,519
- Better than it was.
- And the Ring?

1203
01:58:06,063 --> 01:58:08,565
You feel its power growing, don't you?

1204
01:58:09,066 --> 01:58:11,985
I've felt it too.
You must be careful now.

1205
01:58:12,402 --> 01:58:16,323
Evil will be drawn to you
from outside the Fellowship.

1206
01:58:16,490 --> 01:58:19,076
And, I fear, from within.

1207
01:58:21,703 --> 01:58:25,874
- Who then do I trust?
- You must trust yourself.

1208
01:58:26,041 --> 01:58:28,919
Trust your own strengths.

1209
01:58:29,086 --> 01:58:31,672
- What do you mean?
- There are many powers in this world...

1210
01:58:31,880 --> 01:58:33,924
...for good or for evil.

1211
01:58:34,091 --> 01:58:36,385
Some are greater than I am.

1212
01:58:36,927 --> 01:58:40,555
And against some I have not yet
been tested.

1213
01:58:41,932 --> 01:58:43,308
The walls...

1214
01:58:44,017 --> 01:58:46,103
...of Moria.

1215
01:58:51,817 --> 01:58:54,820
Dwarf doors are invisible when closed.

1216
01:58:55,028 --> 01:58:59,449
GANDALF: Their own masters cannot find
them if their secrets are forgotten.

1217
01:58:59,825 --> 01:59:02,327
Why doesn't that surprise me?

1218
01:59:10,335 --> 01:59:13,630
Well, let's see.

1219
01:59:13,839 --> 01:59:15,215
Ithildin.

1220
01:59:15,841 --> 01:59:19,219
It mirrors only starlight
and moonlight.

1221
01:59:33,275 --> 01:59:37,362
It reads, "The Doors of Durin,
Lord of Moria.

1222
01:59:37,946 --> 01:59:42,576
- Speak, friend, and enter."
- What do you suppose that means?

1223
01:59:42,784 --> 01:59:47,581
It's simple. If you are a friend, you speak
the password and the doors will open.

1224
01:59:48,123 --> 01:59:51,585
[GANDALF SPEAKS IN ELVISH]

1225
02:00:11,313 --> 02:00:12,481
Nothing's happening.

1226
02:00:19,488 --> 02:00:23,700
I once knew every spell
in all the tongues of Elves...

1227
02:00:24,034 --> 02:00:26,828
...Men and Orcs.

1228
02:00:27,120 --> 02:00:28,330
What are you going to do, then?

1229
02:00:28,538 --> 02:00:30,791
Knock your head against these doors,
Peregrin Took!

1230
02:00:31,041 --> 02:00:33,001
And if that does not shatter them...

1231
02:00:33,210 --> 02:00:35,921
...and I am allowed a little peace
from foolish questions...

1232
02:00:36,087 --> 02:00:39,549
...I will try to find the opening words.

1233
02:00:40,008 --> 02:00:43,887
[GANDALF SPEAKS IN ELVISH
AND DWARVISH]

1234
02:00:52,395 --> 02:00:54,940
Mines are no place for a pony.

1235
02:00:55,148 --> 02:00:59,236
- Even one so brave as Bill.
- Bye-bye, Bill.

1236
02:01:00,403 --> 02:01:03,198
Go on, Bill. Go on.

1237
02:01:03,740 --> 02:01:07,285
Don't worry, Sam,
he knows the way home.

1238
02:01:14,084 --> 02:01:16,670
Do not disturb the water.

1239
02:01:16,878 --> 02:01:18,755
Oh, it's useless.

1240
02:01:31,434 --> 02:01:33,603
It's a riddle.

1241
02:01:36,356 --> 02:01:39,484
"Speak 'friend' and enter."

1242
02:01:39,860 --> 02:01:42,779
What's the Elvish word for "friend"?

1243
02:01:44,239 --> 02:01:45,574
<i>Mellon.</i>

1244
02:02:03,592 --> 02:02:08,471
GIMLI: Soon, Master Elf, you will enjoy
the fabled hospitality of the Dwarves.

1245
02:02:08,930 --> 02:02:14,644
Roaring fires, malt beer,
ripe meat off the bone!

1246
02:02:16,146 --> 02:02:19,232
This, my friend,
is the home of my cousin Balin.

1247
02:02:19,608 --> 02:02:21,985
And they call it a mine.

1248
02:02:22,193 --> 02:02:24,154
A mine!

1249
02:02:25,196 --> 02:02:28,533
This is no mine. It's a tomb.

1250
02:02:32,787 --> 02:02:34,247
GIMLI:
No.

1251
02:02:34,664 --> 02:02:36,249
No...

1252
02:02:37,500 --> 02:02:39,169
No!

1253
02:02:41,796 --> 02:02:43,340
Goblins.

1254
02:02:47,260 --> 02:02:51,556
We make for the Gap of Rohan.
We should never have come here.

1255
02:02:52,641 --> 02:02:55,185
ARAGORN:
Now, get out of here. Get out!

1256
02:02:57,979 --> 02:03:00,357
MERRY: Frodo!
FRODO: Help!

1257
02:03:00,565 --> 02:03:02,192
Strider!

1258
02:03:02,359 --> 02:03:05,153
FRODO: Help!
SAM: Get off him!

1259
02:03:05,320 --> 02:03:06,363
Aragorn!

1260
02:03:16,790 --> 02:03:17,832
Frodo!

1261
02:03:19,000 --> 02:03:20,585
Strider!

1262
02:03:44,192 --> 02:03:45,235
Into the mines!

1263
02:03:45,402 --> 02:03:48,613
-Legolas!
ARAGORN: Into the cave!

1264
02:03:52,909 --> 02:03:54,703
Run!

1265
02:04:11,553 --> 02:04:15,140
GANDALF:
We now have but one choice.

1266
02:04:15,348 --> 02:04:20,228
We must face the long dark of Moria.

1267
02:04:20,478 --> 02:04:22,439
Be on your guard.

1268
02:04:22,647 --> 02:04:26,109
There are older
and fouler things than Orcs...

1269
02:04:26,276 --> 02:04:29,821
...in the deep places of the world.

1270
02:04:37,787 --> 02:04:41,750
Quietly now. It's a four-day journey
to the other side.

1271
02:04:41,916 --> 02:04:45,754
Let us hope that our presence
may go unnoticed.

1272
02:05:31,549 --> 02:05:35,261
The wealth of Moria is not in gold...

1273
02:05:35,428 --> 02:05:37,847
...or jewels...

1274
02:05:38,014 --> 02:05:41,059
...but mithril.

1275
02:05:59,410 --> 02:06:04,332
Bilbo had a shirt of mithril rings
that Thorin gave him.

1276
02:06:04,541 --> 02:06:08,503
- Oh, that was a kingly gift.
- Yes.

1277
02:06:08,670 --> 02:06:10,588
I never told him...

1278
02:06:10,755 --> 02:06:15,718
...but its worth was greater than
the value of the Shire.

1279
02:06:28,064 --> 02:06:29,774
Pippin.

1280
02:06:50,461 --> 02:06:53,089
I have no memory of this place.

1281
02:06:55,175 --> 02:06:56,676
PIPPIN: Are we lost?
MERRY: No.

1282
02:06:56,885 --> 02:06:59,387
PIPPIN: I think we are.
MERRY: Gandalf's thinking.

1283
02:06:59,554 --> 02:07:01,014
PIPPIN: Merry?
MERRY: What?

1284
02:07:01,306 --> 02:07:03,266
PIPPIN:
I'm hungry.

1285
02:07:14,569 --> 02:07:19,032
- There's something down there.
- It's GOLLUM.

1286
02:07:19,240 --> 02:07:23,369
- Go||um?
- He's been following us for three days.

1287
02:07:23,578 --> 02:07:27,749
- He escaped the dungeons of Barad-dflr?
- Escaped...

1288
02:07:28,416 --> 02:07:30,084
...or was set loose.

1289
02:07:30,585 --> 02:07:34,255
Now the Ring has brought him here.

1290
02:07:36,883 --> 02:07:39,594
He will never be rid of his need for it.

1291
02:07:39,761 --> 02:07:45,558
He hates and loves the Ring,
as he hates and loves himself.

1292
02:07:45,725 --> 02:07:50,605
Sméagol's life is a sad story.

1293
02:07:50,772 --> 02:07:56,736
Yes, Sméagol he was once called.
Before the Ring found him.

1294
02:07:57,612 --> 02:08:00,448
Before it drove him mad.

1295
02:08:00,740 --> 02:08:03,618
It's a pity Bilbo didn't kill him
when he had the chance.

1296
02:08:03,785 --> 02:08:04,994
Pity?

1297
02:08:06,079 --> 02:08:08,957
It is pity that stayed Bilbo's hand.

1298
02:08:09,874 --> 02:08:15,088
Many that live deserve death.
Some that die deserve life.

1299
02:08:16,506 --> 02:08:18,967
Can you give it to them, Frodo'?

1300
02:08:21,427 --> 02:08:25,390
Do not be too eager
to deal out death and judgment.

1301
02:08:25,598 --> 02:08:28,476
Even the very wise
cannot see all ends.

1302
02:08:29,102 --> 02:08:34,983
My heart tells me that GOLLUM has some
part to play yet, for good or ill...

1303
02:08:35,817 --> 02:08:38,653
...before this is over.

1304
02:08:40,154 --> 02:08:43,992
The pity of Bilbo
may rule the fate of many.

1305
02:08:50,665 --> 02:08:54,002
I wish the Ring
had never come to me.

1306
02:08:55,461 --> 02:08:57,505
I wish none of this had happened.

1307
02:08:57,672 --> 02:09:02,719
So do all who live to see such times.
But that is not for them to decide.

1308
02:09:03,511 --> 02:09:09,017
All we have to decide is what to do
with the time that is given to us.

1309
02:09:10,518 --> 02:09:14,522
There are other forces at work in this
world, Frodo, besides the will of evil.

1310
02:09:14,939 --> 02:09:17,358
Bilbo was meant to find the Ring.

1311
02:09:17,859 --> 02:09:22,196
In which case,
you also were meant to have it.

1312
02:09:22,363 --> 02:09:25,533
And that is an encouraging thought.

1313
02:09:28,494 --> 02:09:29,662
Ah!

1314
02:09:30,455 --> 02:09:32,373
It's that way.

1315
02:09:32,540 --> 02:09:34,876
-He's remembered.
GAN DALF: No.

1316
02:09:35,043 --> 02:09:38,880
But the air doesn't smell
so foul down here.

1317
02:09:39,047 --> 02:09:44,260
If in doubt, Meriadoc,
always follow your nose.

1318
02:09:59,067 --> 02:10:03,237
Let me risk a little more light.

1319
02:10:07,909 --> 02:10:09,994
Behold...

1320
02:10:10,411 --> 02:10:15,625
...the great realm
and Dwarf-city of Dwarrowdelf.

1321
02:10:18,086 --> 02:10:21,547
There's an eye opener, and no mistake.

1322
02:10:46,447 --> 02:10:48,157
Gimli!

1323
02:10:53,955 --> 02:10:55,415
No.

1324
02:10:55,623 --> 02:10:57,250
No!

1325
02:10:59,794 --> 02:11:02,964
Oh, no.

1326
02:11:04,799 --> 02:11:06,092
No.

1327
02:11:13,349 --> 02:11:15,351
GANDALF:
"Here lies Balin...

1328
02:11:15,810 --> 02:11:17,812
...son of Fundin...

1329
02:11:18,146 --> 02:11:20,773
...Lord of Moria."

1330
02:11:21,816 --> 02:11:23,484
He is dead, then.

1331
02:11:25,653 --> 02:11:26,863
It's as I feared.

1332
02:11:38,166 --> 02:11:39,834
[GIMLI SPEAKS DWARVISH]

1333
02:11:45,173 --> 02:11:48,092
We must move on. We cannot linger.

1334
02:11:48,301 --> 02:11:53,014
GANDALF: "They have taken the bridge
and the second hall.

1335
02:11:54,098 --> 02:11:56,684
We have barred the gates...

1336
02:11:57,351 --> 02:11:59,854
...but cannot hold them for long.

1337
02:12:00,021 --> 02:12:02,857
The ground shakes.

1338
02:12:03,232 --> 02:12:04,859
Drums...

1339
02:12:05,193 --> 02:12:08,613
...drums in the deep.

1340
02:12:12,158 --> 02:12:14,202
We cannot get out.

1341
02:12:16,204 --> 02:12:20,041
A Shadow moves in the dark.

1342
02:12:21,709 --> 02:12:24,253
We cannot get out.

1343
02:12:27,256 --> 02:12:29,217
They are coming."

1344
02:12:32,386 --> 02:12:34,222
[CLATTERING]

1345
02:12:51,656 --> 02:12:54,951
[THUDDING]

1346
02:13:00,873 --> 02:13:02,583
[SILENCE]

1347
02:13:12,260 --> 02:13:14,095
Fool of a Took!

1348
02:13:14,428 --> 02:13:18,266
Throw yourself in next time,
and rid us of your stupidity.

1349
02:13:21,894 --> 02:13:24,772
[DRUMS BEATING]

1350
02:13:34,949 --> 02:13:37,326
[SCREECHING]

1351
02:13:44,208 --> 02:13:45,835
SAM:
Frodo!

1352
02:13:48,129 --> 02:13:49,630
Orcs.

1353
02:13:56,637 --> 02:13:58,639
Get back! Stay close to Gandalf!

1354
02:14:05,938 --> 02:14:07,732
They have a cave-troll.

1355
02:14:23,497 --> 02:14:24,665
Let them come!

1356
02:14:25,166 --> 02:14:28,753
There is one Dwarf yet in Moria
who still draws breath.

1357
02:14:43,893 --> 02:14:45,770
[SCREECHES]

1358
02:16:47,641 --> 02:16:50,394
I think I'm getting the hang of this.

1359
02:16:55,149 --> 02:16:56,817
Frodo!

1360
02:17:30,351 --> 02:17:32,186
FRODO:
Aragorn! Aragorn!

1361
02:17:33,187 --> 02:17:35,064
Frodo!

1362
02:18:20,234 --> 02:18:22,111
Frodo!

1363
02:18:24,905 --> 02:18:26,365
Frodo!

1364
02:19:22,338 --> 02:19:23,631
Oh, no.

1365
02:19:26,467 --> 02:19:27,968
[FRODO GROANS]

1366
02:19:32,056 --> 02:19:33,933
He's alive.

1367
02:19:36,352 --> 02:19:39,355
I'm all right. I'm not hurt.

1368
02:19:39,647 --> 02:19:41,857
You should be dead.

1369
02:19:42,066 --> 02:19:44,568
That spear would have skewered
a Wild boar.

1370
02:19:44,818 --> 02:19:49,573
I think there's more to this Hobbit
than meets the eye.

1371
02:19:55,371 --> 02:19:56,497
Mithril.

1372
02:19:59,291 --> 02:20:01,877
You are full of surprises,
Master Baggins.

1373
02:20:02,336 --> 02:20:05,339
[SCREECHING]

1374
02:20:07,883 --> 02:20:09,843
To the Bridge of Khazad-dflm!

1375
02:20:24,817 --> 02:20:26,402
ARAGORN:
This way!

1376
02:21:10,029 --> 02:21:12,072
[GROWLING]

1377
02:21:36,805 --> 02:21:39,808
What is this new devilry?

1378
02:21:53,947 --> 02:21:55,741
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

1379
02:21:55,908 --> 02:21:58,702
A Balrog.

1380
02:21:58,994 --> 02:22:02,122
A demon of the ancient world.

1381
02:22:04,333 --> 02:22:06,794
This foe is beyond any of you.

1382
02:22:07,961 --> 02:22:09,505
Run!

1383
02:22:16,845 --> 02:22:18,347
Quickly!

1384
02:22:34,988 --> 02:22:36,240
Gandalf.

1385
02:22:36,865 --> 02:22:38,492
Lead them on, Aragorn.

1386
02:22:39,868 --> 02:22:42,371
The bridge is near.

1387
02:22:42,621 --> 02:22:44,248
[BALROG GROWLS]

1388
02:22:44,456 --> 02:22:48,544
Do as I say!
Swords are no more use here.

1389
02:23:17,698 --> 02:23:19,408
Gandalf!

1390
02:23:37,718 --> 02:23:38,927
BOROMIR:
Merry! Pippin!

1391
02:23:50,063 --> 02:23:51,565
Sam!

1392
02:23:54,318 --> 02:23:57,571
Nobody tosses a Dwarf.

1393
02:24:00,574 --> 02:24:02,034
Not the beard!

1394
02:24:15,255 --> 02:24:17,132
Steady.

1395
02:24:19,259 --> 02:24:20,928
Hold on!

1396
02:24:23,889 --> 02:24:25,766
[BALROG GROWLS]

1397
02:24:26,850 --> 02:24:28,769
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

1398
02:24:41,949 --> 02:24:43,158
Hang on!

1399
02:24:53,961 --> 02:24:55,671
Lean forward!

1400
02:24:58,632 --> 02:24:59,675
Steady.

1401
02:25:01,009 --> 02:25:02,177
Come on!

1402
02:25:02,427 --> 02:25:03,929
Now!

1403
02:25:21,154 --> 02:25:22,948
Over the bridge!

1404
02:25:23,156 --> 02:25:24,700
Fly!

1405
02:26:09,369 --> 02:26:11,413
You cannot pass!

1406
02:26:11,580 --> 02:26:13,206
Gandalf!

1407
02:26:17,461 --> 02:26:22,341
I am a servant of the Secret Fire,
wielder of the flame of Anor.

1408
02:26:23,342 --> 02:26:27,095
The dark fire will not avail you,
flame of UdGn!

1409
02:26:37,105 --> 02:26:39,066
Go back to the Shadow.

1410
02:26:46,907 --> 02:26:51,370
You shall not pass!

1411
02:27:18,522 --> 02:27:22,401
BOROMIR: No! No!
- Gandalf!

1412
02:27:30,075 --> 02:27:32,536
Fly, you fools!

1413
02:27:36,665 --> 02:27:38,834
No!

1414
02:27:44,965 --> 02:27:47,134
Aragorn!

1415
02:28:44,399 --> 02:28:47,235
Legolas, get them up.

1416
02:28:51,364 --> 02:28:53,200
Give them a moment, for pity's sake!

1417
02:28:53,366 --> 02:28:56,995
By nightfall, these hills will
be swarming with Orcs.

1418
02:28:57,204 --> 02:29:00,540
We must reach the woods of Lothlérien.

1419
02:29:01,416 --> 02:29:04,711
Come, Boromir. Legolas.
Gimli, get them up.

1420
02:29:06,213 --> 02:29:08,423
On your feet, <i>Sam.</i>

1421
02:29:08,757 --> 02:29:10,258
Frodo?

1422
02:29:12,344 --> 02:29:14,054
Frodo!

1423
02:30:06,565 --> 02:30:09,109
Stay close, young Hobbits!

1424
02:30:09,818 --> 02:30:13,947
They say that a great sorceress
lives in these woods.

1425
02:30:14,197 --> 02:30:16,741
An Elf-witch...

1426
02:30:17,284 --> 02:30:20,120
...of terrible power.

1427
02:30:20,704 --> 02:30:22,914
All who look upon her...

1428
02:30:23,123 --> 02:30:24,916
...fall under her spell.

1429
02:30:25,125 --> 02:30:26,418
FEMALE VOICE:
<i>Frodo!</i>

1430
02:30:28,670 --> 02:30:30,714
And are never seen again.

1431
02:30:30,922 --> 02:30:35,427
FEMALE VOICE: <i>Your coming to us is
as the footsteps of doom.</i>

1432
02:30:35,635 --> 02:30:39,306
<i>You bring great evil here,
Ring-bearer.</i>

1433
02:30:39,514 --> 02:30:41,308
SAM:
Mr. Frodo?

1434
02:30:46,605 --> 02:30:52,152
Well, here's one Dwarf
she won't ensnare so easily.

1435
02:30:52,360 --> 02:30:56,948
I have the eyes of a hawk
and the ears of a fox.

1436
02:31:04,623 --> 02:31:09,169
The Dwarf breathes so loud,
we could have shot him in the dark.

1437
02:31:14,341 --> 02:31:16,384
[IN ELVISH]
Welcome Legolas, son of Thranduil.

1438
02:31:17,260 --> 02:31:19,971
[IN ELVISH]
Our Fellowship stands in your debt.

1439
02:31:22,766 --> 02:31:24,476
Aragorn of the Dunedain...

1440
02:31:25,101 --> 02:31:26,519
you are known to US.

1441
02:31:27,354 --> 02:31:29,648
So much for the legendary courtesy
of the Elves!

1442
02:31:29,814 --> 02:31:31,691
Speak words we can all understand!

1443
02:31:31,858 --> 02:31:36,488
[IN ENGLISH] We have not had dealings
with the Dwarves since the Dark Days.

1444
02:31:36,780 --> 02:31:39,282
And you know what this Dwarf
says to that?

1445
02:31:39,699 --> 02:31:42,869
[SPEAKS IN DWARVISH]

1446
02:31:46,206 --> 02:31:48,166
That was not so courteous.

1447
02:31:54,714 --> 02:31:58,718
You bring great evil with you.

1448
02:32:00,512 --> 02:32:02,722
You can go no further.

1449
02:32:08,853 --> 02:32:12,732
[SPEAKING IN ELVISH]

1450
02:32:39,968 --> 02:32:42,595
Gandalf's death was not in vain.

1451
02:32:43,763 --> 02:32:45,640
Nor would he have you give up hope.

1452
02:32:47,142 --> 02:32:50,478
You carry a heavy burden, Frodo.

1453
02:32:51,354 --> 02:32:54,441
Don't carry the weight of the dead.

1454
02:32:57,444 --> 02:32:59,446
You will follow me.

1455
02:33:11,166 --> 02:33:13,126
Caras Galadhon.

1456
02:33:13,793 --> 02:33:16,755
The heart of Elvendom on earth.

1457
02:33:16,921 --> 02:33:22,594
Realm of the Lord Celeborn
and of Galadriel, Lady of Light.

1458
02:34:41,589 --> 02:34:44,717
The enemy knows you have entered here.

1459
02:34:45,385 --> 02:34:50,557
What hope you had in secrecy
is now gone.

1460
02:34:52,267 --> 02:34:56,729
Eight there are here, yet nine there
were set out from Rivendell.

1461
02:34:56,980 --> 02:34:58,773
Tell me, where is Gandalf?

1462
02:34:58,982 --> 02:35:02,068
For I much desire to speak with him.

1463
02:35:02,235 --> 02:35:05,071
I can no longer see him from afar.

1464
02:35:05,905 --> 02:35:11,077
GALADRIEL: Gandalf the Grey did not
pass the borders of this land.

1465
02:35:11,369 --> 02:35:13,788
He has fallen into Shadow.

1466
02:35:18,501 --> 02:35:23,006
He was taken by both Shadow and flame.

1467
02:35:24,632 --> 02:35:28,386
A Balrog of Morgoth.

1468
02:35:29,095 --> 02:35:32,432
For we went needlessly
into the net of Moria.

1469
02:35:34,601 --> 02:35:37,812
Needless were none of the deeds
of Gandalf in life.

1470
02:35:38,438 --> 02:35:41,774
We do not yet know his full purpose.

1471
02:35:46,529 --> 02:35:50,825
Do not let the great emptiness
of Khazad-dflm fill your heart...

1472
02:35:51,117 --> 02:35:53,453
...Gim|I, son of Gléin.

1473
02:35:54,454 --> 02:35:57,957
For the world has grown
full of peril...

1474
02:35:59,459 --> 02:36:02,128
...and in all lands...

1475
02:36:02,295 --> 02:36:05,798
...love is now mingled with grief.

1476
02:36:18,436 --> 02:36:21,147
What now becomes of this Fellowship?

1477
02:36:21,648 --> 02:36:24,651
Without Gandalf, hope is lost.

1478
02:36:27,654 --> 02:36:30,949
The quest stands upon the edge
of a knife.

1479
02:36:31,115 --> 02:36:34,160
Stray but a little and it will fail...

1480
02:36:34,953 --> 02:36:37,789
...to the ruin of all.

1481
02:36:42,126 --> 02:36:47,966
Yet hope remains
while the Company is true.

1482
02:36:49,509 --> 02:36:54,180
Do not let your hearts be troubled.
Go now and rest...

1483
02:36:54,681 --> 02:36:58,351
...for you are weary with sorrow
and much toil.

1484
02:37:00,603 --> 02:37:02,689
Tonight, you will sleep...

1485
02:37:02,855 --> 02:37:06,317
GALADRIEL:
<i>Welcome, Frodo of the Shire...</i>

1486
02:37:07,860 --> 02:37:09,696
<i>...one who has seen the Eye!</i>

1487
02:37:12,198 --> 02:37:15,034
[SINGING IN ELVISH]

1488
02:37:24,335 --> 02:37:26,879
A lament for Gandalf.

1489
02:37:34,178 --> 02:37:35,722
What do they say about him?

1490
02:37:35,930 --> 02:37:38,558
I have not the heart to tell you.

1491
02:37:41,352 --> 02:37:43,563
For me, the grief is still too near.

1492
02:37:46,566 --> 02:37:49,402
I bet they don't mention his fireworks.

1493
02:37:49,569 --> 02:37:52,572
There should be a verse about them.

1494
02:37:56,159 --> 02:37:58,161
<i>The finest rockets ever seen</i>

1495
02:37:59,245 --> 02:38:02,081
<i>They burst in stars of blue and green</i>

1496
02:38:03,041 --> 02:38:06,461
<i>Or after thunder, silver showers</i>

1497
02:38:06,711 --> 02:38:08,755
[GIMLI SNORES]

1498
02:38:08,921 --> 02:38:11,758
<i>Came falling like a rain of flowers</i>

1499
02:38:11,924 --> 02:38:15,803
Oh, that doesn't do them justice
by a long road.

1500
02:38:26,606 --> 02:38:29,275
ARAGORN:
Take some rest.

1501
02:38:29,484 --> 02:38:32,195
These borders are well-protected.

1502
02:38:32,403 --> 02:38:34,947
I will find no rest here.

1503
02:38:37,784 --> 02:38:40,787
I heard her voice inside my head.

1504
02:38:40,995 --> 02:38:44,749
<i>She spoke of my father
and the fa“ of Gender.</i>

1505
02:38:44,957 --> 02:38:50,421
She said to me,
"Even now there is hope left."

1506
02:38:51,798 --> 02:38:54,634
But I cannot see it.

1507
02:38:55,968 --> 02:38:58,471
It is long since we had any hope.

1508
02:39:08,648 --> 02:39:10,775
My father is a noble man.

1509
02:39:11,526 --> 02:39:13,778
But his rule is failing...

1510
02:39:14,112 --> 02:39:19,492
...and our people lose faith.

1511
02:39:20,952 --> 02:39:24,497
He looks to me to make things right,
and I would do it.

1512
02:39:24,664 --> 02:39:28,167
I would see the glory
of Gondor restored.

1513
02:39:31,003 --> 02:39:34,006
Have you ever seen it, Aragorn?

1514
02:39:34,674 --> 02:39:36,676
The White Tower of Ecthelion.

1515
02:39:36,843 --> 02:39:40,680
Glimmering like a spike
of pearl and silver.

1516
02:39:41,347 --> 02:39:44,851
Its banners caught high
in the morning breeze.

1517
02:39:47,770 --> 02:39:49,730
Have you ever been called home...

1518
02:39:49,897 --> 02:39:53,860
...by the clear ringing
of silver trumpets?

1519
02:39:54,485 --> 02:39:57,697
I have seen the White City...

1520
02:39:58,030 --> 02:39:59,532
...long ago.

1521
02:40:00,533 --> 02:40:05,496
One day, our paths will lead us there.

1522
02:40:06,414 --> 02:40:09,375
And the tower guard
shall take up the call:

1523
02:40:09,834 --> 02:40:13,171
<i>“The Lords of Gender have returned.“</i>

1524
02:41:20,363 --> 02:41:22,907
Will you look into the mirror?

1525
02:41:23,074 --> 02:41:24,617
What will I see?

1526
02:41:27,578 --> 02:41:29,914
Even the wisest cannot tell.

1527
02:41:30,790 --> 02:41:32,625
For the mirror...

1528
02:41:32,875 --> 02:41:35,419
...shows many things.

1529
02:41:38,422 --> 02:41:40,800
Things that were...

1530
02:41:41,008 --> 02:41:43,594
...things that are...

1531
02:41:44,387 --> 02:41:46,305
...and some things...

1532
02:41:49,892 --> 02:41:53,187
...that have not yet come to pass.

1533
02:42:57,084 --> 02:42:59,587
[VOICES SPEAKING IN BLACK SPEECH]

1534
02:43:15,728 --> 02:43:18,564
I know what it is you saw.

1535
02:43:21,025 --> 02:43:23,527
For it is also in my mind.

1536
02:43:25,279 --> 02:43:29,367
<i>It is what will come to pass
if you should fail.</i>

1537
02:43:31,744 --> 02:43:36,582
<i>The Fellowship is breaking.
It is already begun.</i>

1538
02:43:37,249 --> 02:43:40,544
<i>He will try to take the Ring.</i>

1539
02:43:40,753 --> 02:43:42,755
<i>You know of whom I speak.</i>

1540
02:43:43,756 --> 02:43:48,427
<i>One by one, it will destroy them all.</i>

1541
02:43:49,929 --> 02:43:52,390
<i>FRODO:
If you ask it of me...</i>

1542
02:43:52,765 --> 02:43:55,810
<i>...I will give you the One Ring.</i>

1543
02:43:56,894 --> 02:43:59,063
You offer it to me freely.

1544
02:44:03,609 --> 02:44:07,571
I do not deny that my heart
has greatly desired this.

1545
02:44:13,953 --> 02:44:17,248
In place of a Dark Lord,
you would have a queen...

1546
02:44:17,665 --> 02:44:21,460
...not dark but beautiful,
and terrible as the dawn!

1547
02:44:22,128 --> 02:44:25,131
Treacherous as the sea!

1548
02:44:25,631 --> 02:44:30,594
Stronger than the foundations
of the earth!

1549
02:44:31,053 --> 02:44:33,431
All shall love me...

1550
02:44:33,639 --> 02:44:36,475
...and despair.

1551
02:44:50,573 --> 02:44:54,869
I pass the test. I will diminish...

1552
02:44:55,161 --> 02:44:57,621
...and go into the West...

1553
02:44:57,830 --> 02:45:02,293
- ...and remain Galadriel.
- I cannot do this alone.

1554
02:45:05,880 --> 02:45:10,009
You are a Ring-bearer, Frodo.
To bear a Ring of Power...

1555
02:45:10,968 --> 02:45:12,470
...is to be alone.

1556
02:45:15,806 --> 02:45:18,517
This is Neo ya,
the Ring of Adamant.

1557
02:45:18,726 --> 02:45:20,352
And I am its keeper.

1558
02:45:23,522 --> 02:45:27,193
This task was appointed to you.

1559
02:45:28,194 --> 02:45:31,113
And if you do not find a way...

1560
02:45:32,323 --> 02:45:34,325
...no one will.

1561
02:45:34,700 --> 02:45:37,870
Then I know what I must do.

1562
02:45:38,537 --> 02:45:39,705
It's just...

1563
02:45:43,000 --> 02:45:45,211
...I'm afraid to do it.

1564
02:45:48,714 --> 02:45:53,886
Even the smallest person can change
the course of the future.

1565
02:45:59,225 --> 02:46:04,939
Do you know how the Orcs
first came into being?

1566
02:46:05,731 --> 02:46:09,068
They were Elves once.

1567
02:46:10,236 --> 02:46:13,572
Taken by the Dark Powers...

1568
02:46:13,739 --> 02:46:16,909
...tortured and mutilated.

1569
02:46:17,243 --> 02:46:22,581
A ruined and terrible form of life.

1570
02:46:22,873 --> 02:46:24,708
And now...

1571
02:46:26,168 --> 02:46:28,045
...perfected.

1572
02:46:28,754 --> 02:46:31,924
My fighting Uruk-hai...

1573
02:46:33,884 --> 02:46:36,220
...whom do you serve?

1574
02:46:36,428 --> 02:46:38,931
Saruman!

1575
02:46:59,785 --> 02:47:03,247
Hunt them down. Do not stop
until they are found.

1576
02:47:03,455 --> 02:47:06,333
You do not know pain.
You do not know fear.

1577
02:47:06,584 --> 02:47:09,461
You will taste Man-flesh!

1578
02:47:14,592 --> 02:47:18,304
One of the half lings carries
something of great value.

1579
02:47:18,470 --> 02:47:22,641
Bring them to me alive and unspoiled.

1580
02:47:24,476 --> 02:47:25,769
Kill the others.

1581
02:47:44,955 --> 02:47:50,377
CELEBORN: Never before have we clad
strangers in the garb of our own people.

1582
02:47:51,503 --> 02:47:55,341
May these cloaks help shield you
from unfriendly eyes.

1583
02:48:02,514 --> 02:48:04,058
Lembas.

1584
02:48:04,308 --> 02:48:05,893
Elvish way bread.

1585
02:48:08,395 --> 02:48:11,398
One small bite is enough to fill
the stomach of a grown man.

1586
02:48:17,863 --> 02:48:19,865
How many did you eat?

1587
02:48:20,032 --> 02:48:21,700
<i>Four.</i>

1588
02:48:23,202 --> 02:48:26,205
[BELCHES]

1589
02:48:27,498 --> 02:48:30,084
CELEBORN: <i>Every league you travel south,
the danger will increase.</i>

1590
02:48:30,292 --> 02:48:34,380
<i>Mordor Ores now hold the eastern shore
of the Anduin.</i>

1591
02:48:34,546 --> 02:48:37,049
<i>Nor will you find safety
on the western bank.</i>

1592
02:48:37,299 --> 02:48:41,095
Strange creatures bearing the White Hand
have been seen on our borders.

1593
02:48:41,303 --> 02:48:46,392
Seldom do Orcs journey in the open
under the sun, yet these have done so.

1594
02:48:55,067 --> 02:48:57,695
[IN ELVISH]
You are being tracked.

1595
02:48:59,071 --> 02:49:00,322
[IN ENGLISH]
By river you have the chance...

1596
02:49:00,489 --> 02:49:03,701
...of outrunning the enemy
to the Falls of Rauros.

1597
02:49:20,968 --> 02:49:25,764
GALADRIEL: My gift for you, Legolas,
is a bow of the Galadhrim.

1598
02:49:26,056 --> 02:49:29,560
Worthy of the skill
of our woodland kin.

1599
02:49:34,940 --> 02:49:37,401
These are the daggers of the Noldorin.

1600
02:49:37,568 --> 02:49:40,779
They have already seen service in war.

1601
02:49:40,946 --> 02:49:43,991
Do not fear, young Peregrin Took.

1602
02:49:44,158 --> 02:49:47,453
<i>You will find your courage.</i>

1603
02:49:49,371 --> 02:49:51,331
<i>And for you, Samwise Gamgee...</i>

1604
02:49:51,498 --> 02:49:54,084
...Elven rope made of hithlain.

1605
02:49:54,251 --> 02:49:56,378
Thank you, my lady.

1606
02:49:58,172 --> 02:50:01,508
Have you run out
of those nice, shiny daggers?

1607
02:50:07,973 --> 02:50:10,976
And what gift would a dwarf ask
of the Elves?

1608
02:50:11,143 --> 02:50:13,312
Nothing.

1609
02:50:13,937 --> 02:50:17,274
Except to look upon the lady
of the Galadhrim one last time...

1610
02:50:17,900 --> 02:50:23,113
...for she is more fair
than all the jewels beneath the earth.

1611
02:50:30,162 --> 02:50:31,705
Actually...

1612
02:50:31,914 --> 02:50:33,499
There was one thing.

1613
02:50:34,333 --> 02:50:37,002
No, no, I'm talking nonsense.
It's quite impossible.

1614
02:50:37,169 --> 02:50:40,005
<i>Stupid to ask.</i>

1615
02:50:42,508 --> 02:50:44,676
GALADRIEL:
<i>I have nothing greater to give...</i>

1616
02:50:44,843 --> 02:50:48,430
...than the gift you already bear.

1617
02:50:49,640 --> 02:50:50,682
[IN ELVISH]
For her love,

1618
02:50:51,975 --> 02:50:57,314
I fear the grace of Arwen Evenstar
will diminish.

1619
02:50:58,065 --> 02:51:01,401
[IN ELVISH]
I would have her leave these shores,

1620
02:51:02,945 --> 02:51:05,864
and be with her people.

1621
02:51:07,866 --> 02:51:13,580
I would have her take the ship to Valinor.

1622
02:51:14,081 --> 02:51:17,167
[IN ENGLISH]
That choice is yet before her.

1623
02:51:17,751 --> 02:51:20,671
You have your own choice to make,
Aragorn.

1624
02:51:21,004 --> 02:51:26,844
To rise above the height of all
your fathers since the days of Elendil...

1625
02:51:27,010 --> 02:51:31,348
...or to fall into darkness
with all that is left of your kin.

1626
02:51:38,480 --> 02:51:39,857
[IN ELVISH]
Farewell.

1627
02:51:43,652 --> 02:51:47,030
There is much you have yet to do.

1628
02:51:53,537 --> 02:51:54,788
We shall not meet again...

1629
02:51:54,997 --> 02:51:56,373
Elessar.

1630
02:51:58,917 --> 02:52:02,087
<i>[IN</i> ENGLISH]
<i>Farewell, Frodo Baggins.</i>

1631
02:52:02,254 --> 02:52:05,716
I give you the light of Eérendil...

1632
02:52:06,425 --> 02:52:08,760
...our most beloved star.

1633
02:52:17,936 --> 02:52:22,316
<i>May it be a light for you
in dark places...</i>

1634
02:52:22,566 --> 02:52:26,653
<i>...when all other lights go out.</i>

1635
02:52:35,454 --> 02:52:38,624
GIMLI: I have taken my worst wound
at this parting...

1636
02:52:39,291 --> 02:52:43,587
...having looked my last upon that
which is fairest.

1637
02:52:44,296 --> 02:52:47,633
Henceforth I will call nothing fair
unless it be her gift to me.

1638
02:52:47,925 --> 02:52:49,843
What was her gift?

1639
02:52:50,052 --> 02:52:54,973
I asked her for one hair
from her golden head.

1640
02:52:55,766 --> 02:52:58,644
She gave me three.

1641
02:54:04,167 --> 02:54:07,546
[BIRDS SQUAWKING]

1642
02:54:40,787 --> 02:54:44,249
GOLLUM. He has tracked us since Moria.

1643
02:54:47,961 --> 02:54:51,089
I had hoped we would lose him
on the river.

1644
02:54:51,298 --> 02:54:54,468
But he's too clever a water man.

1645
02:54:55,302 --> 02:54:58,597
And if he alerts the enemy
to our whereabouts...

1646
02:54:58,764 --> 02:55:01,058
...it will make the crossing
even more dangerous.

1647
02:55:01,224 --> 02:55:03,268
SAM:
Have some food, Mr. Frodo.

1648
02:55:03,435 --> 02:55:06,563
- No, <i>Sam.</i>
- You haven't eaten anything all day.

1649
02:55:06,730 --> 02:55:09,816
You're not sleeping, neither.
Don't think I haven't noticed.

1650
02:55:10,776 --> 02:55:13,779
- Mr. Frodo--
- I'm all right.

1651
02:55:13,945 --> 02:55:15,113
But you're not.

1652
02:55:15,405 --> 02:55:17,908
I'm here to help you.

1653
02:55:18,075 --> 02:55:19,785
I promised Gandalf that I would.

1654
02:55:25,749 --> 02:55:28,460
You can't help me, <i>Sam.</i>

1655
02:55:30,629 --> 02:55:32,339
Not this time.

1656
02:55:35,258 --> 02:55:37,344
Get some sleep.

1657
02:55:43,683 --> 02:55:45,811
<i>M'mas meh “vs the safer road.</i>

1658
02:55:46,311 --> 02:55:49,106
You know that.
From there we can regroup.

1659
02:55:49,773 --> 02:55:51,983
Strike out for Mordor from a place
of strength.

1660
02:55:52,317 --> 02:55:55,237
There is no strength in Gondor
that can avail us.

1661
02:55:55,654 --> 02:55:57,656
You were quick enough to trust
the Elves.

1662
02:55:59,533 --> 02:56:02,369
Have you so little faith
in your own people?

1663
02:56:02,536 --> 02:56:05,539
Yes, there is weakness.
There is frailty.

1664
02:56:05,747 --> 02:56:09,042
But there is courage also,
and honor to be found in Men.

1665
02:56:09,292 --> 02:56:11,503
But you will not see that.

1666
02:56:11,837 --> 02:56:13,255
You are afraid!

1667
02:56:13,505 --> 02:56:16,049
All your life, you have hidden
in the shadows.

1668
02:56:16,341 --> 02:56:19,803
Scared of who you are,
of what you are.

1669
02:56:22,180 --> 02:56:26,560
I will not lead the Ring within
a hundred leagues of your city.

1670
02:56:38,405 --> 02:56:39,781
Frodo.

1671
02:56:41,658 --> 02:56:43,160
The Argonath.

1672
02:56:46,580 --> 02:56:50,333
Long have I desired
to look upon the kings of old.

1673
02:56:51,042 --> 02:56:53,003
My kin.

1674
02:58:11,957 --> 02:58:14,167
We cross the lake at nightfall.

1675
02:58:14,417 --> 02:58:16,962
Hide the boats and continue on foot.

1676
02:58:17,170 --> 02:58:20,632
- We approach Mordor from the North.
- Oh, yes?

1677
02:58:21,091 --> 02:58:24,928
Just a simple matter of finding
our way through Emyn Muil...

1678
02:58:25,095 --> 02:58:28,306
...an impassable labyrinth
of razor-sharp rocks.

1679
02:58:28,515 --> 02:58:31,643
And after that, it gets even better.

1680
02:58:32,018 --> 02:58:36,982
Festering, stinking marshland
as far as the eye can see.

1681
02:58:37,148 --> 02:58:38,525
That is our road.

1682
02:58:40,110 --> 02:58:43,321
I suggest you take some rest
and recover your strength, Master Dwarf.

1683
02:58:43,530 --> 02:58:45,282
Recover my--

1684
02:58:48,285 --> 02:58:50,287
- We should leave now.
- No.

1685
02:58:50,453 --> 02:58:54,916
Orcs patrol the eastern shore.
We must wait for cover of darkness.

1686
02:58:55,125 --> 02:58:58,545
It is not the eastern shore
that worries me.

1687
02:58:58,795 --> 02:59:02,799
A shadow and a threat
has been growing in my mind.

1688
02:59:03,300 --> 02:59:07,470
Something draws near.
I can feel it.

1689
02:59:09,472 --> 02:59:14,436
Recover strength?
Pay no heed to that, young Hobbit.

1690
02:59:14,936 --> 02:59:16,646
Where's Frodo?

1691
02:59:42,255 --> 02:59:44,174
BOROMIR:
None of us should wander alone.

1692
02:59:45,550 --> 02:59:47,677
You, least of all.

1693
02:59:47,886 --> 02:59:50,347
So much depends on you.

1694
02:59:51,389 --> 02:59:53,350
Frodo?

1695
03:00:00,482 --> 03:00:03,026
I know why you seek solitude.

1696
03:00:03,735 --> 03:00:07,197
You suffer. I see it day by day.

1697
03:00:07,989 --> 03:00:11,034
You sure you do not suffer needlessly?

1698
03:00:12,577 --> 03:00:15,246
There are other ways, Frodo.

1699
03:00:15,497 --> 03:00:19,292
- Other paths that we might take.
- I know what you would say.

1700
03:00:19,542 --> 03:00:23,296
It would seem like wisdom
but for the warning in my heart.

1701
03:00:23,546 --> 03:00:26,591
Warning? Against what?

1702
03:00:26,800 --> 03:00:28,927
We're all afraid, Frodo.

1703
03:00:29,135 --> 03:00:32,764
But to let that fear drive us,
to destroy what hope we have...

1704
03:00:33,014 --> 03:00:36,768
- ...don't you see that is madness?
- There is no other way.

1705
03:00:38,561 --> 03:00:41,898
I ask only for the strength
to defend my people!

1706
03:00:43,441 --> 03:00:45,527
- If you would but lend me the Ring.
- No.

1707
03:00:46,736 --> 03:00:50,407
- Why do you recoil? I am no thief.
- You are not yourself.

1708
03:00:52,242 --> 03:00:55,578
What chance do you think you have?

1709
03:00:55,745 --> 03:01:00,417
They will find you.
They will take the Ring.

1710
03:01:00,625 --> 03:01:04,337
And you will beg for death
before the end!

1711
03:01:06,464 --> 03:01:08,591
You fool!

1712
03:01:08,758 --> 03:01:12,762
It is not yours, save by unhappy chance!
It could have been mine.

1713
03:01:12,929 --> 03:01:15,765
It should be mine! Give it to me!

1714
03:01:15,932 --> 03:01:17,267
- Give it to me!
- No!

1715
03:01:17,434 --> 03:01:19,269
- Give it to me!
- No.

1716
03:01:26,943 --> 03:01:28,945
I see your mind.

1717
03:01:29,154 --> 03:01:32,115
You will take the Ring to Sauron!

1718
03:01:32,323 --> 03:01:34,200
You will betray us!

1719
03:01:34,451 --> 03:01:37,620
You'll go to your death,
and the death of us all!

1720
03:01:38,079 --> 03:01:41,708
Curse you!
Curse you and all the half lings!

1721
03:01:48,798 --> 03:01:50,300
Frodo?

1722
03:01:54,637 --> 03:01:56,181
Frodo.

1723
03:02:00,143 --> 03:02:02,145
What have I done?

1724
03:02:02,353 --> 03:02:04,105
Please, Frodo.

1725
03:02:04,314 --> 03:02:06,983
Frodo, I'm sorry!

1726
03:02:07,192 --> 03:02:09,027
Frodo!

1727
03:02:34,344 --> 03:02:37,680
[VOICE OF THE RING
SPEAKS IN BLACK SPEECH]

1728
03:02:55,532 --> 03:02:56,950
Frodo?

1729
03:02:58,201 --> 03:03:01,287
- It has taken Boromir.
- Where is the Ring?

1730
03:03:01,538 --> 03:03:03,289
Stay away!

1731
03:03:03,706 --> 03:03:05,291
Frodo!

1732
03:03:07,544 --> 03:03:11,381
- I swore to protect you.
- Can you protect me from yourself?

1733
03:03:21,057 --> 03:03:23,560
Would you destroy it?

1734
03:03:28,565 --> 03:03:30,483
VOICE OF THE RING:
<i>Aragorn.</i>

1735
03:03:33,903 --> 03:03:36,239
<i>Aragorn.</i>

1736
03:03:38,074 --> 03:03:39,909
<i>Elessar.</i>

1737
03:03:47,584 --> 03:03:50,920
I would have gone with you to the end.

1738
03:03:51,588 --> 03:03:54,424
Into the very fires of Mordor.

1739
03:03:57,760 --> 03:03:58,928
I know.

1740
03:04:01,431 --> 03:04:06,853
Look after the others. Especially <i>Sam.</i>
He will not understand.

1741
03:04:10,607 --> 03:04:12,317
Go, Frodo!

1742
03:04:15,320 --> 03:04:16,821
Run.

1743
03:04:17,113 --> 03:04:18,781
Run!

1744
03:04:43,306 --> 03:04:44,974
Mr. Frodo!

1745
03:04:54,275 --> 03:04:56,027
Find the half ling!

1746
03:04:57,654 --> 03:05:00,198
Find the half ling!

1747
03:05:03,660 --> 03:05:05,328
Elendil!

1748
03:05:11,834 --> 03:05:13,378
Aragorn, go!

1749
03:05:35,108 --> 03:05:36,401
PIPPIN:
Frodo!

1750
03:05:37,026 --> 03:05:38,611
Hide here. Quick!

1751
03:05:39,237 --> 03:05:40,697
Come on!

1752
03:05:43,199 --> 03:05:45,201
What's he doing?

1753
03:05:49,414 --> 03:05:51,416
He's leaving.

1754
03:05:56,212 --> 03:05:59,132
- No!
- Pippin!

1755
03:06:04,053 --> 03:06:06,389
MERRY:
Run, Frodo. Go on!

1756
03:06:06,931 --> 03:06:10,059
- Hey! Hey, you!
- Over here!

1757
03:06:10,435 --> 03:06:12,061
- Over here!
- This way!

1758
03:06:22,905 --> 03:06:25,241
- It's working!
- I know it's working! Run!

1759
03:07:18,711 --> 03:07:20,338
[HORN BLOWS]

1760
03:07:20,630 --> 03:07:23,674
- The horn of Gondor.
- Boromir.

1761
03:08:06,759 --> 03:08:07,885
Run!

1762
03:09:44,649 --> 03:09:47,068
[ARROW HITS]

1763
03:11:39,472 --> 03:11:41,098
No.

1764
03:11:44,935 --> 03:11:47,980
- They took the little ones.
- Hold still.

1765
03:11:48,272 --> 03:11:50,399
Frodo. Where is Frodo?

1766
03:11:52,276 --> 03:11:53,694
I let Frodo go.

1767
03:11:54,403 --> 03:11:56,947
Then you did what I could not.

1768
03:11:57,948 --> 03:12:01,285
I tried to take the Ring from him.

1769
03:12:01,786 --> 03:12:06,123
- The Ring is beyond our reach now.
- Forgive me.

1770
03:12:06,290 --> 03:12:08,626
I did not see it.

1771
03:12:08,793 --> 03:12:11,962
- I have failed you all.
- No, Boromir.

1772
03:12:12,463 --> 03:12:14,965
You fought bravely.

1773
03:12:15,299 --> 03:12:17,968
You have kept your honor.

1774
03:12:18,511 --> 03:12:20,471
BOROMIR:
Leaveit

1775
03:12:20,805 --> 03:12:22,807
It is over.

1776
03:12:24,016 --> 03:12:29,313
The world of Men will fall.
And all will come to darkness...

1777
03:12:29,730 --> 03:12:32,733
...and my city to ruin.

1778
03:12:36,821 --> 03:12:39,490
I do not know what strength
is in my blood...

1779
03:12:39,657 --> 03:12:43,661
...but I swear to you,
I will not let the White City fall...

1780
03:12:44,662 --> 03:12:47,164
...nor our people fail.

1781
03:12:48,165 --> 03:12:49,500
Our people.

1782
03:12:53,337 --> 03:12:55,506
Our people.

1783
03:13:17,194 --> 03:13:20,197
I would have followed you, my brother.

1784
03:13:21,782 --> 03:13:23,784
My captain.

1785
03:13:26,370 --> 03:13:28,372
My king.

1786
03:13:48,017 --> 03:13:50,227
Be at peace...

1787
03:13:50,561 --> 03:13:52,563
<i>...son of Gender.</i>

1788
03:14:09,079 --> 03:14:12,416
They will look for his coming
from the White Tower.

1789
03:14:12,917 --> 03:14:15,920
But he will not return.

1790
03:14:39,109 --> 03:14:41,111
Frodo!

1791
03:15:00,631 --> 03:15:03,884
FRODO: <i>I wish the Ring had never</i> come <i>to me.</i>

1792
03:15:05,135 --> 03:15:08,138
<i>I wish none of this had happened.</i>

1793
03:15:11,141 --> 03:15:13,894
<i>GANDALF: So do all who live
to see such times...</i>

1794
03:15:14,103 --> 03:15:17,523
<i>...but that is not for them to decide.</i>

1795
03:15:17,690 --> 03:15:20,317
<i>All you have to decide...</i>

1796
03:15:20,609 --> 03:15:25,322
...is what to do with the time
that is given to you.

1797
03:15:54,184 --> 03:15:56,186
Frodo, no!

1798
03:15:56,729 --> 03:15:58,022
Frodo!

1799
03:15:58,856 --> 03:16:01,525
- Mr. Frodo!
- No, <i>Sam.</i>

1800
03:16:05,029 --> 03:16:07,031
Go back, Sam!

1801
03:16:07,531 --> 03:16:11,160
- I'm going to Mordor alone.
- Of course you are.

1802
03:16:11,368 --> 03:16:14,204
And I'm coming with you!

1803
03:16:14,663 --> 03:16:17,041
You can't swim!

1804
03:16:20,878 --> 03:16:22,546
Sam!

1805
03:16:28,177 --> 03:16:29,470
Sam!

1806
03:17:10,427 --> 03:17:13,097
I made a promise, Mr. Frodo.

1807
03:17:13,430 --> 03:17:17,768
A promise:
"Don't you leave him, Samwise Gamgee."

1808
03:17:18,936 --> 03:17:21,522
And I don't mean to.

1809
03:17:21,772 --> 03:17:23,941
I don't mean to.

1810
03:17:25,609 --> 03:17:27,444
<i>Sam.</i>

1811
03:17:42,292 --> 03:17:43,961
Come on.

1812
03:18:12,489 --> 03:18:16,994
Hurry! Frodo and Sam
have reached the eastern shore.

1813
03:18:31,842 --> 03:18:36,847
- You mean not to follow them.
- Frodo's fate is no longer in our hands.

1814
03:18:40,350 --> 03:18:45,189
Then it has all been in vain.
The Fellowship has failed.

1815
03:18:57,034 --> 03:19:00,204
Not if we hold true to each other.

1816
03:19:01,538 --> 03:19:06,043
We will not abandon Merry and Pippin
to torment and death.

1817
03:19:07,044 --> 03:19:12,341
Not while we have strength left.
Leave all that can be spared behind.

1818
03:19:13,550 --> 03:19:15,636
We travel light.

1819
03:19:15,844 --> 03:19:17,721
Let us hunt some Orc.

1820
03:19:20,724 --> 03:19:22,726
Yes!

1821
03:19:41,745 --> 03:19:43,163
FRODO:
Mordor.

1822
03:19:43,747 --> 03:19:47,167
I hope the others find a safer road.

1823
03:19:48,085 --> 03:19:50,671
Strider will look after them.

1824
03:19:51,588 --> 03:19:54,925
I don't suppose
we'll ever see them again.

1825
03:19:55,259 --> 03:19:57,761
We may yet, Mr. Frodo.

1826
03:19:57,928 --> 03:19:59,471
We may.

1827
03:20:01,598 --> 03:20:02,599
Sam...

1828
03:20:06,270 --> 03:20:08,897
...I'm glad you are with me.

1829
03:48:05,989 --> 03:48:07,991
[English - US - SDH]

